Order ID- 1023217, 1023201

OGW order ID - 2083900. 2083873

Environment - ACC1

1. Login to telesales channel
2. Add FusionC package
3. Submit order
4. Verify OneDMS fast search interface triggered first empty response
5. Verify that Fast search request is not retriggered even though first empty response is received.

*Actual Result -* For FusionC telesales activation orders OGW is not retriggering fast search request after receiving first empty response.
 

*Expected Result -* For FusionC telesales activation orders OGW should successfully retrigger fast search request after receiving first empty response.

column1: Z_PRT00158847A | OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | OPT | Mobile new activation orders with more than two package is stuck at Credit Evaluation steps in KIAS
column41:
Hello 

 

We've encountered with our Mobile Private New Activation orders that include more than two packages. It seems these orders are getting stuck at the Credit Evaluation step in KIAS. As discussed and confirmed by the KIAS Test Team, the current reference data indicates that KIAS supports a maximum of two packages activation for Individual (Private) customer types.
 
In the past, with previous OSF releases, the activation process worked smoothly for more than four packages for Private customers. In the current release, we also have test cases that include more than two packages. Could you please check and confirm what the expected behavior should be in this scenario?

Test Data:
BAN: 119051560
 
Env: ACC1/VOLAPP17

 

 

We have created this issue for tracking PRT Z_PRT00158747A

GLS discontinued its GLSIDENT service some time ago (months ago). For security reasons, we didn't immediately deactivate it in Prod, but instead made it "unselectable" via PriceRange adjustments. It was finally deactivated now (in Prod and Test). Unfortunately, the PriceRange in Test hadn't been adjusted at the time, so since yesterday, the old service for items up to €600 hasn't been available, only new services. We've now corrected the PriceRange in Test as well, and an old service is being returned via the GASO.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Production Deliveries | RequestSimSwapRequest is not getting triggered for esim Push Orders
column41:
Issue: While performing Esim Push Orders, we have observed that RequestSimSwapRequest is not getting triggered.

Order Details: 1022119/16003568

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Telesales channel…Perform legacy search on the customer…Load the customer.
 # Click on Standard Prolongation option.
 # Add new eSIM capable hw and new Tariff and optionen (with OneNumber as PhysicalSIM (pSIM)).
 # Proceed to checkout…Fill all the necessary details.
 # Select the SimType as eSIM (for main tariff) and enable eSIM-Push. (Note: Because of new eSIM capable hw and depending on existing SIM, the OSF-frontend will automatically select a new eSIM with eSIM-Push in OSF frontend)
 # Select The Ultracard SimType as PhysicalSim.
 # Submit the order…Verify OGW logs.

Actual Result: RequestSimSwapRequest is not getting trigerred.

Expected Result: RequestSimSwapRequest should trigger.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Retail | UM | Production Deliveries | Agent entered TAN code and clicks "Prüfen" option then getting technical error
column41:
ACC1 Retail channel once "{*}Email Verification"{*} is success  and TAN code is sent to respective email as well and once agent reached to TAN code page, after entering the TAN code and  clicks "Prüfen" option then getting technical error.

*Steps To Re-produce:*

1) Login to retail channel in ACC1 environment

2) Search the UM address

3) Check the serviceability 

4) Click the Kabel Internet and Phone option and select KIP products

5) Click the "Zum checkout" 

6) Fill the mandatory customer information and Valid *Email id* , 

7) Click the *"Email verification" button* and check email verification success response and TAN code is send to respective email.

8) Proceed the order till TAN code page

9) Enter the TAN code received to email id and click *"Prüfen"* 

10) Once Agent clicks the *"Prüfen"* then check TAN code validation success or getting error

 

*Expected Results:*

Agent Once entered the Valid  TAN code and click the *"Prüfen"* then TAN code validation should be success response.

*Actual Results:* 

Once Agent enters the valid TAN code received to email id and click *"Prüfen"* then TAN code validation not success and or getting error

 

Error First Click: *Code-Verifizierung nicht möglich. Bitte versuche es später noch einmal. (Timeout)*

Second Click: *Ein technischer Fehler ist aufgetreten. Bitte versuche es später erneut oder kontaktiere den Support, falls das Problem weiterhin besteht. Contact Medium already verified, Verification time 2025-09-19T07:13:14+02:00*

 

*Note:* Even we are getting above error but Agent Still can able to submit the order

hi [~elango.durairaj@vodafone.com] 
When we trigger any DXL service ,the Oauth is called to get a bearer token and once received it will be stored in OSF redis cache such that if the same DXL call triggered again the token is taken from cache( if its available) instead of calling the Oauth again.

Please verify once by clearing cache;;;

 * Shival Gupta, Vodafone (External) suggested checking the Contact Medium Verification Timeout settings in ACC1 Backoffice (BO).also recommended verifying these settings.

column878:
16/Sep/25 12:46 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;RCA: According to this ticket [VFDED2W90S-222: Omnius_Config: As a system, I want to save sim type flag for hardware selected so that I can enable relevant checkout fields [OS-46432]Done|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED2W90S-222#icft=VFDED2W90S-222] the requirement specifies that when a hardware device is selected with SIM compatibility as eSIM, pSIM, both, or blank/null, Omnius must save the corresponding flag at the package level:

eSIMHW for eSIM
pSIMHW for pSIM
bothSIMHW for both
NoSIMInfo for blank/null

However, in PCAT, the SIM Compatibility field was left blank/null, and the implementation failed to handle this edge case.

The code did not include logic to handle cases where SIM_COMPATIBILITY is blank or null. The current logic only handles explicitly defined values (eSIM, pSIM, both) and skips validation for empty value.;;;

column883:
16/Sep/25 5:22 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;On VFP side nothing was changed!

This issue seems to be related to the PST bug: [[PSTBUG-3509] PAPI | OSF | VKD,VFW | All orders are failing with Delivery & Billing address error message - DE Jira|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PSTBUG-3509]

Answer from developer:

Hello,
The issue is in IBP (IRIS) when it contacts AdsFacade to validate the sent addresses. The exact field causing the issue is houseNumberAddition. When the field is omitted in the request, AdsFacade returns an asterisk in the candidate addresses. When the address is compared with the candidate address returned from AdsFacade, the validation fails (becasue null != '*'). 
A workaround can be applied in IRIS to ignore asterisks in both the address and the candidate address when comparing them as it's already a wildcard.

[~anna-mariya.robeto@vodafone.com] could you please update us as soon as the PST bug is solved. The PST bug was created only fr test1b, but we have this issue on all ACC environments. Thank you;;;

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 
[~thomas.wermke@vodafone.com] added a comment - [Yesterday|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-76802?focusedId=3830108&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-3830108] - edited
Todays meeting with TechM and ACC-Team revealed that this issue is NO bug.
it is based more or less on a misunderstanding about the different PCAT setups for Telesales and Retail scenarios.

1. The purpose of the affected PCAT Compatibility Rule is to force an agent/user belonging to a Retail sales channel to select an sku from the category of retail blister(i.e. a SIM card item or eSIM cardboard card physically available in the shop).

2. During test execution, a clear distinction must be made between the agent’s affiliation with a particular sales channel and the login process on the respective Telesales or Retail websites.

3. Unfortunately the above mentioned rule cannot be restricted to the webite "Retail". Instead it evaluates the agent’s affiliation with a particular sales channel.

4. The current Prepaid product configuration in PCAT for Telesales restricts tariff selection to the predefined set of Telesales-specific SKUs (formatted as 'Kso' + <KIAS-TO-code>). Upon selection, a corresponding SIM/blister/item is automatically added to the shopping cart in a one-to-one relationship. Manual selection of alternative products or tariffs by the user is not permitted in this flow. After checkout, the order is transmitted to SAP, which initiates the dispatch of a pre-activated SIM card to the customer via mail.
 
5. The updated Prepaid product setup in PCAT for Retail enables the selection of both a blister item and a tariff from the available set of Retail tariffs (SKUs formatted as 'K' + <KIAS-TO-code>). Typically, the user first selects a blister item, after which a default tariff —usually the one printed on the packaging and defined in the KIAS table PREPAID_PACKAGE for the selected item_id— is automatically pre-selected. The user then has the option to deselect and change this default tariff and choose an alternative from the list of available tariffs, as defined in the KIAS table ACTIVATION_SETTINGS for the selected item_id. Upon checkout, the retail agent hands the blister/SIM to the customer, and the order is transmitted to the KIAS backend for subscriber activation. Especially in this scenario, it is important to use PCAT rules to force the user to select a blister and a tariff before checkout. 

-> Telesales user/sales id should belong to a Telesales channel (not the website) and a blister item is added automatically to the shopping cart after tariff selection.
Retail user/sales id should belong to a Retail channel (Filiale, Fachhandel, Partneragentur) and a tariff is preselected after blister selection.Manual choice of a blister is mandatory.

-> Tickets OS-77100, OS-76802, OS-76950 should be rejected and cancelled.;;;

h2.

Steps To Reproduce:
 # Login to Telesales
 # Configure mobile package with PSIM compactible H/W
 # do checkout
 # select Store ident
 # submit order
 # Process order from VORAS

 

{*}Expected Result{*}:  OGW is should send final PushOrder status as "CompletedSuccess" for Ship to store with PSIM orders.

{*}Actual Result{*}:  OGW is not sending final PushOrder status as "CompletedSuccess" for Ship to store with PSIM orders.
column324: S2S orders with PSIM will not be completed in telesales channel.
column569: Additional handling was added for Ship to Store status as part of  Z_PRT00158558A
column874: 14/Aug/25 4:40 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;currently per OGW logic, for voras status: VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT, when order line is not ESIM, OGW will not send completed success;;;
column875:
15/Aug/25 4:35 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;We have shared this feedback with Brigitta and Rob but as per them, Independent if eSim or pSim must the order be set to completed after status VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT in ship-to-store flow.

Email communication is ongoing;;;
column876: 19/Aug/25 5:10 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;no further update received so far, how we are going to handle it;;;
column877: 24/Aug/25 7:09 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;asked for update how to handle this defect via email;;;
column878:
27/Aug/25 11:51 AM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Email Feedback from Monday from Rob:

Waldemar has created an overview of  use-cases and status changes last week

I will invite to a call with Brigitta and Waldemar, so we have a clear view from VF side.  Then I will invite to a call with Amdocs

My current assumption: we have identified a lot of OGW designgaps, that were already in production BEFORE the Esim Push  project and this could be another one; perhaps it was never explicitly documented / tested and therefore OGW sets the wrong status.

 ;;;

column41:

As per story:[OS-43047] OMNIUS_CHCK_As Omnius I want to introduce new DXL Digital Identity Management (contactMediumVerification) interface to call or initiate request towards DXL for email verification so that email captured by Agent during Checkout can be verified (OS-43047) - Vodafone Global Jira

*Expected Result:*

{              "name": "stack",                "value": "um"             },    

 

Adding the logs in the comments
column569:
RCA:- In scenarios involving the Broad Vision offering, the Cable TV package is automatically added alongside the KIP package. As per the current implementation logic, the contract subdivision value within the catalog package is only set during the configurator product loading process.
In certain flows, particularly when the user proceeds directly to checkout without loading the Cable TV package in the configurator, the contract subdivision value is not set in the associated table. As a result, the system misclassifies the package under the Cable instead of the intended UME.

column324: Agent not able to do leagacy serach for Cable customer
column569:
(Resolution) What was done to fix the issue?
The new Fabric target group Ip's registered and the old ones deregistered .

(Root Cause) What caused the issue?
The Target group ip were pointing to old ips , that cause the issue.

(Prevention) What preventive actions should be taken?

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | S2S Order is getting completed success without waiting for final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer in Telesales channel.
column41:
In this case the EVT_040 from SAP means that the hardware was delivered to the shop. At this point in time it is not clear, if the customer will pick the hardware or not. The EVT_040 with location type VF_STORE therefore has to be “ignored”. Instead OSF has to wait for the following final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer. This process was implemented with project eSim Push and also needs to be used for device financing. The loan activation may only be triggered, when the final sale was done in VORAS.

Steps to re-produce:
1. Login to telesales channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. fill all customer details
4. select shiptostore
5. check out
6. submit order

{*}Actual Result{*}: OGW is calling SIM Swap request for S2S order without waiting for final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer in Telesales channel.

{*}Expected result{*}: Status InProgress-HWFulfilmentReady with VF_STORE should be ignored in OGW. 

*Order Details:*

Omnius ID: 1002307
OGW ID: 2052900

 

{color:#ff8b00}*This issue observed only in Telesales channel.*{color}

column874:
08/Aug/25 12:41 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~sneha.wayal1@vodafone.com] ,


1.  In this case *(SimCard=E, ActivtyType=New),* OGW calls RequestSimSwap after the subscriber is activated in KIAS, this behavior aligns with the design and is functioning as expected.

2. Upon receiving *EVT_040* with *SAPLocationType = VFSTORE,* OGW appropriately ignored it and awaited the *VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT* event to proceed with loanActivation and subsequently mark the orderLine as completed.

However instead of VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT, OGW received an addition *EVT_040* for the same orderLine {*}without SAPLocationType as VFSTORE{*}, which is incorrect and also the reason for processing this status, as OGW neither received the SAPLocationType nor the EID. Attaching both the setOrderStatus EVT_040 for your reference. 

i. First EVT_040 with SAPLocationType=VFSTORE:

ii. Second EVT_040 without SAPLocationType:

added a comment -
 
Hi Sneha/Gokul,


According to our investigations though the call, if the value VF_STORE is present in the SAP Status file then we transfer it to OGW. If it is not present then we also do not proceed with it. Thus, the RCA is either the value was not initially present in the SAP file or was present twice: with and without value.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 l ACC1 | Pipeline is missing in SAP file before the VFStore value for S2S without EID scenario.
column41:
Hello,

I can see one pipeline is missing before the VFStore value from SAP. As a result, Omnius is taking VFStore as the EID Number since it's present in the EID Number place. Due to this issue, Omnius is sending the Attribute value VFStore in the Attribute code EID in “InProgress-HWFulfilmentReady” SetOrderStatus to OGW. Therefore, OGW is not waiting for the final status from VORAS and completing the flow.

!image-2025-08-06-09-46-02-290.png|width=776,height=28!

*SetOrderStatus Logs from Omnius to OGW:*

 <DATA>

   <OGWSubOrderId>2048888</OGWSubOrderId>

   <OGWOrderLineId>1007114514</OGWOrderLineId>

   <Status>InProgress-HWFulfilmentReady</Status>

   <AdditionalInfo>

     <AttributeCode>SapOrderID</AttributeCode>

     <AttributeValue>c718783b7d</AttributeValue>

   </AdditionalInfo>

   <AdditionalInfo>

     *<AttributeCode>EID</AttributeCode>*

     *<AttributeValue>VFSTORE</AttributeValue>*

   </AdditionalInfo>

Steps to reproduce:
1. Loging to retail channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. Select Ship to store as delivery method
4. Generate DF contract document
5. Submit the order

Expected Result: Location type should be sent in SAP file.

Actual Result: Location type is missing in Ship to store SAP file.

Note: . In case of Ship to store in the status file the location type should be VF_STORE. But this is missing

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | MSISDN first digit is getting merged in NDC value in NDC_MSISDN tag in send session request for Online ident in telesales channel.
column41:
We observe that MSISDN first digit is merged with NDC value in send session request for Online ident in telesales channel.

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Login into Telesales.
 # Add mobile postpaid package.
 # Add Tariff and Hardware
 # Fill required details and select online ident as identification method.
 # Submit the order.

 

*Actual Result:* First digit of MSISDN is getting merged in NDC value
<value>0174{*}7{*}_{*}289873{*}</value>

NDC length should be less than 4 and MSISDN Length is min 7.

*Expected result:* MSISDN no. should not be merged in NDC value

it should be like Example: *174_7289873* separated with '_'

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Total monthly tariff charges are being displayed in two separate lines even though the overall total charge remains the same for DeviceFinancing tariff with 12, 24, and 36 months DF duration
column41:
Hello,

We observed in DeviceFinacing tariff with 12, 24 and 36 months DF duration, the monthly totals on mobile (tariff) bill shows two lines, although the total charge is not different.

order id: 994443

As there is no need for showing the customer, that he must pay different prices for the VF service during his contract period, there is also no need to show this part  “Monat 1 - XX”  and   “ab Monat  [XX+1])
Exactly as it is today in production!

Solution/Defect hint: 
As expect that somehow the devicefinancing duration of the  (mobile Mixmatch File:  DeviceFinancingDuration parameter)  is handed overfrom Omnius  to OGW ->  OM  ->  most likely an Omnius defect/design gap

The CR we created a few weeks ago for correcting the mobile contract in case of device financing:
[OS-73799] BUSINESS: CR948: As a sales agent I want the mobile contract to be correct in case of DF tariffs - defect4 - Vodafone Global Jira

The technical stories are linked in this Business story


{*}Steps to reproduce{*}:
1. Loging to retail / telesales channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. Select Ship to store as delivery method
4. Generate DF contract document
5. Submit the order

{*}Actual Result{*}: DeviceFinacing tariff with 12, 24 and 36 months DF duration, the monthly totals on mobile (tariff) bill shows two lines, although the total charge is not different

!image-2025-07-25-17-00-40-766.png|width=685,height=146!

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

 !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 

{*}Expected Result{*}: DeviceFinacing tariff with 12 months DF duration, the monthly totals on mobile (tariff) bill should show single line

!image-2025-07-25-17-01-21-802.png|width=711,height=40!

Note: same issue observed for 12, 24 and 36 month of Device Financing duration.

column876:
28/Jul/25 6:52 PM;nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com;Hello

Below is reply from Rob

I guess Shruti has a point, but I don’t get it.
From  “high level” perspective the mistake is clear to me:
As usual:  if there is only one price, that the customer must pay over the complete contract period  (which is endless for mobile tariffs) , then there is only one total line to be printed  (as we hae done always)
But,  if the decisions, that were made in  the solution design lead to another outcome ( which is the part, that I don’t understand:  requirement was always and still is clear:  in case of device financing NO hardware related stuff to be put on the mobile contract) WHY do we have two lines in the totals, although the total costs do not change?

We will schedule a call for the same;;;
column877: 29/Jul/25 2:17 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Checked with Nasir, Discussion is ongoing between Rob and Shruti, will schedule a call later for this if required;;;
column878:
30/Jul/25 4:34 PM;nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com;Hello,

We had a meeting with Rob, Shruti and Gaurab and below is the outcome of meeting

Hi,

See attached document we created during the call  for defining the algorithm how to remove duplicate line in the Mobile contract in case of device financing

Assumption;  today in  production these duplicate lines do not happen for subsidized tariffs/hardware  and this is only caused by the device financing SKU in the submitOrder

Shruti has stated, that adding this additional logic to the already very complex device financing submitOrder logic might have a severe impact on the performance.

Todo TechM:  align with development team, if the solution as defined in this call is feasible  (and if yes: commicate an expected delivery date)

 [^use-case multiple lines on mobile  bill defect X.docx] ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Non-Device Financing debtor (Payment method ID) is sending in SAP file for Device Financing order
column41:
Hello

While performing mobile new activation  device financing HW and tariff, we observed order are failing in sap file process due to Non-Device Financing debtor is sending in SAP file for Device Financing order

{*}Steps to re-produce{*}:
1. Logging to telesales channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. Add onenumber option
4. Do checkout
5. Generated contract summary
6. Generate contract document
7. Submit order

8.Send for Sap processing

{*}Actual Result{*}: Getting error device financing debtor in sap file.

{*}Expected result{*}: 
When DeviceLoanOrderID is populated with value from PushOrderStatus
The rules engine resulted out come value must map to SAP hardware file correctly. Specially within the RecordType  = 1 (header data) and Column = 74 (K_customer number SAP/K_Kunden_Nr_KIAS)
|*Use case*|*Delivery Method*|*Payment Method*|*CPD account*|*Remark*|
|1|ShipToStore|NA|101711| payment method is actually always:  Cash  (which is not implemented in OSF  ->  from OSF perspective:  payment method is not relevant)|
|2|Other|DirectDebit|101710| |
|3|Other|Invoice|101712| |

Reference story: [OS-60955] Omnius OIL: As a system, I want to generate SAP hardware order for device finance use cases, so that SAP can process the shipment of this hardware [OS-60955] - Vodafone Global Jira

column1: On-Hold | SPN-OPT-000143071 | OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Retail | At a TV tariff change with analog change (KASWAP) with a Service option ONLY on the 2nd package the contract document is not created
column41:
Browser: Chrome

Channel: Retail

Cable PCAT version: V2510_2025_07_00_072

Test customer: 935320753 (TV tariff change allowed and analog product will be changed as well and SN3 in the inventory)

 

*Please note:*

1. if we have only 1 TV package then the Contract Document is opened

!image-2025-07-15-14-23-41-071.png!

!image-2025-07-15-14-23-21-439.png!

2. If we create a new activation with KIP and TV, we also have 2 packages, but here the contract document can also be opened

!image-2025-07-15-14-34-07-549.png!

!image-2025-07-15-14-34-40-899.png!

 

+Actual Result:+ At a TV tariff change with analog change (KASWAP) {*}and on the 2nd package ONLY the service option (SN3/ SN4) stays in the inventory{*}, Contract document is stuck at SPP state in OM

+Expected Result:+ At a TV tariff change with analog change (KASWAP) it should be possible to open the contract document

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * load a Cable TV customer in Retail, e. g.: 935320753 
 * click on "Meine Produkte >> KAD package >> Paket ändern" 
 * select a new TV tariff, e.g.: "[CTWGPNTW1] Vodafone GigaTV Home Cable inklusive Netflix"

        – > "KASWAP" is preselected automatically – > *OK*

!image-2025-07-15-13-56-42-102.png!
 * select a new analog product where ONLY "SN3" will be kept in the 2nd package, e. g.: "[TCM:TW1] Vodafone TV Connect Standard"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * continue with the order until the Contract Summary page
 * click on the button "Drucken"

– > Contract Summary is opened – > *OK*
 * select the checkbox " Die Vertragszusammenfassung wurde besprochen und über SignoSign abgeschlossen"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Drucken"

– > Contract Document is NOT opened – > *NOT OK*

*!image-2025-07-15-14-02-17-123.png!*

23/Jul/25 8:45 PM;alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com;SPN-OPT-000143071 is rejected with below comment:

Hi [Hamza Balci, Vodafone (External)|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hamza.balci1%40vodafone.com] 

wir haben [OMART-466|https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fde.jira.agile.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOMART-466&data=05%7C02%7Cnorbert.forai%40dxc.com%7Cd624ef0bfba24639d87208ddc6027487%7C93f33571550f43cfb09fcd331338d086%7C0%7C0%7C638884436496987768%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=7%2Fh9LoRc%2BK8CfdKGLgws8si%2BqhXqbJgAKG2sbeLrgf0%3D&reserved=0] weiter untersucht und festgestellt, dass die Ursache des Problems darin liegt, dass in der zweiten „PackageConfiguration” vom Typ TV der Knoten „CommercialProducts“ fehlt.

Laut omogw.xsd sollte unter einem PackageConfiguration Knoten mindestens ein Knoten „CommercialProducts“ vorhanden sein.

!image-2025-07-23-20-45-15-966.png!

Sobald mindestens ein Knoten „CommercialProducts“ hinzugefügt wurde, treten keine Probleme bei der Verarbeitung auf (siehe Anhang).

*Wir haben auch die Testdaten überprüft, die dem Produktionsvorfall INC000094827316 beigefügt waren. Dort besteht das gleiche Problem.*

*Da es sich um ein Problem mit den Eingabedaten handelt, sollte im Eingabesystem geprüft werden, warum das System diese Informationen in diesem Szenario nicht an OM weiterleitet.*

FYI: die zweite PackageConfiguration  Knoten kann entfernt werden. Es funktioniert ebenfalls einwandfrei, sofern die erste PackageConfiguration  für TV die aktuellen Details nach der Änderung enthält.

 

Gruß,

Norbert Forai;;;

column883:
25/Jul/25 5:37 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com] ,

OGW includes *CommercialProducts* in a package only when the *LineActivityType* in the *CommercialDetails* (received in the SubmitOrder request from Omnius) is not "{*}REFUSE{*}" or "{*}DROP{*}", and the *ScopeList* contains a Scope with the value "{*}Contract{*}".

For the second package, such CommercialDetails are missing, which is why OGW does not add any CommercialProducts to it.

PFB for reference:

The error mentioned in the below comment is valid. OGW is returning it because we haven't yet received a callback from OM for that specific document. This can be confirmed by checking the status in the OGW_SEND_DOCUMENT_TRANSACTIONS table, which currently shows "Sent to OM". As mentioned earlier as well, OGW includes *CommercialProducts* in a package only when the *LineActivityType* in the *CommercialDetails* (received in the SubmitOrder request from Omnius) is not "{*}REFUSE{*}" or "{*}DROP{*}", and the *ScopeList* contains a Scope with the value "{*}Contract{*}".

For the second package with SkuID {*}SN3{*}, these conditions still appear to be unmet, which is why OGW does not add the CommercialProducts to it.

column569:
There was some change implemented on Portal side which mixed up the connection: the parameter "MinervaClient.uri" is not used any more, but now the new parameters "anypoint.baseUri" and "minervaClient.path" need to be used and configured according to the relevant backends

 ;;;
column876:
10/Jul/25 7:07 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback from portal side:


We (Team Spice) had a change to the logic in MinervaAdapter and how it retrieves the config value for the Minerva URL.

Originally, there was one config value "MinervaClient.uri". We split this into "anypoint.baseUri" and "minervaClient.path"

The currently deployed  new versions of MinervaAdapter already use the baseUri and the path, instead of the uri
 # action: switch the config value for test1b in the WMC and restart MinervaAdapter -> retest failed
 # action: minervaNG is switched and MinervaAdapter restarted -> seems to work now

 

 

We need to get the confirmation that its permanent fix and not only workaround;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Tracking defect for CR899 issue - Agents with existing permission LOCKING_ACCOUNTS are not working properly anymore
column41:
As per implementation of CR 899 - OAF-914, the following behavior is expected

*Behavior*
 * Agents with permission LOCKING_ACCOUNTS are able to view "Sperren" tab and have the ability to lock/unlock accounts (no changes to current implementation)
{color:#de350b}*-> THIS IS BROKEN after CR899 implementation*{color}
 * Agents with new permission VIEW_ACCOUNTS are also able to view the "Sperren" tab with all related information but cannot lock or unlock accounts (the toggle button is greyed out).
 * If both, LOCKING_ACCOUNTS and VIEW_ACCOUNTS permission is accidently assigned to an agent role, the VIEW_ACCOUNTS permission is overriding the LOCKING_ACCOUNTS permission.

 

This defect is tracking defect, as currently there was no ACC test planned for this CR, I was just randomly looking into this CR as TechM already had concerns about their implementation and if it will work correctly

TechM will send a fix for this issue, but this issue avoids go live of CN_19270 to production
column324: It will not be possible to lock or unlock any users anymore
column569:

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | VFW SoHo customer fails with Sky ticket because of missing company name in payer section
column41:
Order for a B2B SoHo customer of Vodafone West footprint: customer UN_806010802
in ACC1 - OrderID: 983281

In attached collection of screenshots it is visible that the company name "Companyname 1" was provided in all relevant addresses:
- Serviceaddress: shows company name
- Delivery address: shows company name
- Billing address: shows company name
- Account owner: shows company name

STILL when sending the order it gets a Sky-Force Ticket with error “Required Input COMPANY_NAME missing” Error code: OGWERR-1408


h2. Assumed root cause - based on check of logs:

=> it is missing in submitOrder/ processOrder requests in:

SourceContact "4" - ContactRole "PC" (Payer Contact)

 
h2. To be checked:

On every new customer order for VFW footprint the value entered in OSF Gui company name field for serviceaddress ist correctly added in all four SourceContact fields <CompanyName>.

On an existing customer the same field is just pre-filled by data loaded from backend.

Why is <ContactRole>PC not also automatically pre-populated with that value - as all other SourceContactIDs are?

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | OGW is completing S2S order without waiting for final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer.
column41:
In this case the EVT_040 from SAP means that the hardware was delivered to the shop. At this point in time it is not clear, if the customer will pick the hardware or not. The EVT_040 with location type VF_STORE therefore has to be “ignored”. Instead OSF has to wait for the following final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer. This process was implemented with project eSim Push and also needs to be used for device financing. The loan activation may only be triggered, when the final sale was done in VORAS.

Steps to re-produce:
1. Logging to telesales/retail channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. fill all customer details
4. select shiptostore
5. check out
6. submit order

{*}Expected result{*}: GW should complet S2S order after final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer.

{*}Actual Result{*}: OGW is completing S2S order without waiting for final status “VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT” which is sent from VORAS after final sale to the customer.

*Note:*

[~gaurab.mitra2@vodafone.com]{color:#de350b} {*}C{*}{*}o{*}{*}uld you please update confluence page for this functionality.{*}{color}

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | PROD REG | TAN code verification failed with technical error
column41:
TAN code verification failed with below error message

{*}Note{*}: There is no delay in entering the TAN code, once email verification done and sent to TAN code to email id, then proceeding the further screen without any delay, but once reaches to TAN code verification field and entering the TAN code( Ex: *082577)*  immediately we are getting TAN code failed with Timeout error/Technical error

*Error 1:* Code-Verifizierung nicht möglich. Bitte versuche es später noch einmal. (Timeout)

*Error 2:* Ein technischer Fehler ist aufgetreten. Bitte versuche es später erneut oder kontaktiere den Support, falls das Problem weiterhin besteht. Contact Medium already verified, Verification time 2025-06-27T06:19:53+02:00

Steps to Reproduce:

1) Login to ACC1 Retail channel

2) Search the UM address and check the serviceability

3) Select the UM Cable product from the configurator

4) Click the checkout

5) Enter all the customer information's ,including valid email id( Ex: elango.durairaj@vodafone.com) and send the TAN code

6) Proceed the further steps in OSF order proceedings

7) Once reached TAN code verification field enter the TAN code 6 digit number(Ex: *082577)* and click

8) Check user able to validate the TAN code and able to submit the order or timeout error/technical error occurring.

 

*Expected Results:* If user continuing the order after sending the TAN code via email verification without any time delay then TAN code verifications should be success and user able to submit the order 

*Actual Results:* TAN code verification failed with below error message Timeout error/Technical error

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Ship to store set order status not received in OGW.
column41:
Hello,

We observed Ship to store set order status not received in OGW.

OGW order id: 2022791

{*}Steps to reproduce{*}:
1. Loging to retail channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. Select Ship to store as delivery method
4. Generate DF contract document

5. Submit the order

{*}Expected Result{*}: Ship to store set order status should be received in OGW.

{*}Actual Result{*}: Ship to store set order status not received in OGW.

 

the setOrderStatus was sent from VORAS-side but could obviously not be handled on OSF-side:

 

2025-06-24 09:21:48,370;ERROR;voras-uat-tomcat1.voras.vode.lan;50020;[OsfOrderItemStatusUpdate Consumer Thread_1750244225073_1213778584994048];(de.vodafone.voras.server.onlinegateway.osf.OsfService.setOrderStatus(OsfService.java:1024)); Functional error received from OSF: Error Code: OGWERR-2000, Error Text: Calling OSF SetOrderStatus webservice failed for ogwOrderId=2022791 and debtorId=0000994010; - Request could not be routed to the appropriate enviroment. Please contact system administrator 
2025-06-24 09:21:48,378;ERROR;voras-uat-tomcat1.voras.vode.lan;84103;[OsfOrderItemStatusUpdate Consumer Thread_1750244225073_1213778584994048];(de.vodafone.voras.server.web service.jms.osf.consumer.OsfOrderItemStatusUpdateConsumerThread.run (OsfOrderItemStatusUpdateConsumerThread.java:232)); OsfOrderItemStatusUpdate has detected an invalid status update message with id

[32.0.0][F4010][L][2022791][1006544229][VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT][1750749697680_1719251192035685].

This message will be ignored forever. Refused data: de.vodafone.voras.common.webservices.interfaces.osf.OsfFunctionalError: OsfFunctionalError.

Error: OGWERR-2000 - Request could not be routed to the appropriate enviroment. Please contact system administrator

 

And this has NOTHING to do with the below defect. The above process is the STANDARD scenario for ship-to-store and NOT a new scenario after S2S not picked up.

column1: Tracking Purpose_OSF | Z_INC02835163A | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | For VKD New Acquistion retail channel contract document is missing in OneDMS
column41:
While performing VKD new activation, after submitting the order and E2E completion. Contract document is missing in One DMS.

Subject - Confirmation needed for Customer: 935317749 for unavailability of document in OneDMS

Issue Details:
1.The Contract_Document is missing.
2.The Contract_Summary is available, but it was archived under the wrong document class ("Vertragsunterlagen eingehend" instead of "ausgehend").

Expected Result:
the expected workflow is as follows:
-OSF / Order System creates the customer order (e.g. Order ID: 976837).
PAReS system processes the order documents (Contract_Summary and Contract_Document) and marks them as ready for archiving.
OGW (Order Gateway) triggers the archiving process and updates the status: ArchiveCableDocuments.
Cable DMS / OneDMS archives the documents in the appropriate document class.
However, only the Contract_Summary was archived — and in the wrong document class (eingehend instead of ausgehend).
The Contract_Document is completely missing, which could indicate a failure in the archiving trigger, routing, or file transfer from PAReS to OneDMS.

Note : FLow - OSF 🡪 Pares 🡪 eFlow 🡪 Iris 🡪 OneDMS

While sending Loan application/cancellation request via postman 405 and 409 error are not coming.

 

URL: https://dxl-preprod.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de:443/osf/v1/orderHandling/v1/productOrder

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Open postman Tool
 # Configure Bearer token
 # send a request POST/GET

*Actual Result:*  Getting 400 Bad request error.

*Expected Result:* Expected Error is 405 and 409.

 

Attaching sample request for loan application and cancellation.

column881:
02/Jul/25 5:19 PM;sneha.wayal1@vodafone.com;*MOM 02/07/2025:*
 * Discussion/Workshop between VF-DE OSF ACC test team & VF-Group GFP team to find a solution how to test the following error codes
 * Error code 405 "Method Not Allowed"
 * This error code is received, when tested via APIX. So, the error code 405 is working as designed in APIX.
 * This error code is +not+ received, when tested via DXL:
 * So, DXL may filter/cover this error code 405 or will prevent a request to APIX by the own DXL-error-logic.
 * So, it must be clarified with DXL ([@Sebastian Schier, Vodafone|mailto:Sebastian.Schier@Vodafone.com]), how DXL is designed for this error code.
 * Alternatively, the error-scenario can be tested direct via APIX
 * For that the APIX credentials have been created via the APIC portal: [Login | Developer Portal|https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fapix.developer.vodafone.com%2Flogin&data=05%7C02%7Csneha.wayal1%40vodafone.com%7Ca341b78487fb4614f94908ddb95c3f53%7C68283f3b84874c86adb3a5228f18b893%7C0%7C0%7C638870528055287022%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=DFDfL8ysgLPAfVOjtiv6Scn1h4%2Fsn2XN%2FslytvlD%2FLk%3D&reserved=0]


 * Error code 409 "The provided OpCo external Identifier already exists"
 * Initially this error code was requested and implemented
 * With another request the implementation was removed, to be able to re-use a request with the same OPCOID, if the first try was failed by any technically reason
 * So, this requirement (error code 409) is obsolete:
 * So, the requirement must be changed/removed
 * So, the test to receive the error code 409 will +not+ be performed


 * VF-DE team confirmed that this topic was never an escalation nor project-critical nor a testing-blocker of any kind.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Incorrect Infotext format printed in contract summary with 36 month Tariff for Device financing orders.
column41:
While performing mobile new activation with Device financing with 36 Month tariff and hardware scenarios, we observed incorrect infotext format (I.e Intotext printed twice in contract summary)for Device financing orders.

Order id: 981033

Steps to reproduce:
1. Loging to retail/telesales channel
2. Configure mobile package with DF tariff and H/W
3. Do checkout|
4. agent has clicked on the "Create Document".
5.CS & CD downloaded
5. Submit order

Expected Result:

-"Summe bei Kündigung des Mobilfunkvertrags n.
Mindestlaufzeit" (Summe bei Kündigung des Mobilfunkvertrags n.
Mindestlaufzeit) Infotext should be printed once I.E for continuation of the mobile phone contract after the minimum term.
 horizonal line  under the individual SKUs of the monthly payment

Actual Result: "Summe bei Kündigung des Mobilfunkvertrags n.Mindestlaufzeit" Printed twice on CS.
                       horizonal line is missing under the individual SKUs of the monthly payments

01/Jul/25 2:23 PM;simran.mogram1@vodafone.com;Retested Infotext 1 " Summe bei Kündigung des Mobilfunkvertrags nach Mindestlaufzeit" is printed correctly in CS.

Regarding Infotext2,  According to OS-73625 Omnius_Submit: CR Omnius_Submit: As a system, I want to modify the existing logic for sending InfoText sent for Device Financing Orders in the Submit Order payload towards OGW OS-73625 - Vodafone Global Jira 
infotext1 will only be visible if and only if *Device Financing Duration > Initial Period of Mobile Tariff*
if {*}Device Financing Duration <= Initial Period of Mobile Tariff{*}, then +Omnius will+ *+NOT+* +send any InfoText (The logic of sending InfoText 2 must be removed from Omnius)

*CS printed correctly for DF customer. Hence close defect.*

column878:
19/Jun/25 7:17 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi All,

We found the issue, in AllocateBanAndCtnResponse in the beginning of fulfillment, KIAS is sending us BAN as "119046735" and the same is updated in the CDM. Whereas in Completed-Success KIAS set_order_status for subscriber Activation, we are receiving a different BAN "119046736". This is resulting in mismatch of subscriberSequence and hence a few mandatory parameters in SetMarketingPermissionsRequest are not being populated as per the implementation. Attaching the AllocateBanAndCtnResponse and the set_order_status received from KIAS for reference. ;;;
column879: 20/Jun/25 12:02 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Hi [~affan.baragazi@vodafone.com] This use case is performed in Telesales channel, Could you please check again as AllocateBanAndCtnRequest should not be called in Telesales channel.;;;
column880:
20/Jun/25 12:59 PM;affan.baragazi@vodafone.com;Hi [~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com],

The AllocateBanAndCtnRequest is invoked in the Telesales channel for the 'NEW' ActivityType. This can be verified via the Confluence documentation, please find the link attached for your reference.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Regression | IPCC order E2E flow not working(RNS frontend "OPT-IN" information not updated)
column41:
IPCC orders Voice files information not updated in to RNS frontend portal for UM scenarios.

 

Steps to Re-Produce:

1: Login to OSF  application with Telesales user in ACC1

2:  Place an order with IPCC flow,

3: Check whether orders is completed in OSF frontend portal.

4: Check whether voice files are  sent.

5: Check Whether OPT-IN options updated in RNS frontend

6: Check in MOOD front end Voice files are available.

 

*Test data:*

NRW: OSF ID-980437, web:6245133 , OGW: 2020903, Customer: 1024251801

Trans ID-Transaction Id : 01a7038e5e2511ad

 

KBW :OSF ID-980441, web:6245135 , OGW:2020910 , Customer: 566488703

Trans ID-01a7038e5e2511ae

 

Actual Results: IPCC E2E order is not working and RNS front end OPT-IN details are not updated

 

Expected Results: RNS frontend OPT-IN details should be reflected.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | OGW is sending O instead of 0 in consentVerificationStatus for Telesales channel  (Mobile & DSL)
column41:
Error:  for Mobile New activation and ILS in Telesale channel facing below error 

<ns:errorDetails><ns:errorCode>EAI002789</ns:errorCode><ns:errorType>Functional</ns:errorType><ns:errorSystem>deopteai06</ns:errorSystem><ns:errorSeverity>E</ns:errorSeverity><ns:errorMessage>value is invalid</ns:errorMessage><ns:errorDescription>value is invalid</ns:errorDescription><ns:errorInformation> '{*}CONSENT_VER_STATUS' is invalid{*}, Backend Error Code: 1144</ns:errorInformation><ns:errorApplication>KIAS</ns:errorApplication>

 

Step to Reproduce:
 # Login to Telesale Channel
 # Place Mobile /DSL with BEW permission
 # Check SetMarketingPermissionsRequest in OGW logs

Expected Result: OGW should send 0 in consentVerificationStatus

 

Actual Result: OGW is sending O instead of 0 in consentVerificationStatus


*NOTE : SetMarketingPermission is failing for Mobile stack due to wrong "O" value instead of "0"   &* 
*no impact on DSL (Even if value is "O" instead of "0", no Sky tickets for DSL and received response from BE)*
*But 0 value is expected here*



Please find attached OMNIUS and OGW request

 

!image-2025-06-17-19-25-54-515.png!

!image-2025-06-17-19-31-49-628.png!
column324:

Telesales/ COPS channel only - for Consumer BEW is currently normally not used in production (Customer confirms CS via email link) - only relevant for SoHo agents who still collect BEW

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Incorrect SIMCard Type is being sent in submit order request for SIM only with MultiSIM use case.
column41:
While performing Mobile New Activation with the SIM Only package including the MultiSIM (Vodafone OneNumber) option in the Telesales channel, we have observed, when selecting ESIM for the Main card and a Physical SIM for the MultiSIM, Omnius is sending an incorrect SIM type in the submit order request for the Main tariff option product.

Omnius is sending SIMCard=N instead of SIMCard=E

Please find below screenshot and attached logs.

!image-2025-06-13-19-03-58-961.png|width=485,height=307!

!image-2025-06-13-19-04-24-000.png|width=483,height=186!

!image-2025-06-13-18-53-45-912.png|width=381,height=333!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid package with SIM only Product and MultiSIM option.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Select ESIM for Main card and Physical SIM for MultiSIM Card.
 # Save SIM Information and Submit order.
 # Check submits order request.

Actual: Incorrect SIMCard Type (N) is being sent in submit order request for SIM only with MultiSIM use case for Main card.

Expected: Correct SIMCard Type (E) should be sent in submit order request for SIM only with MultiSIM use case for Main card.
column324: OIL will not generate an entry for RecordType "02" for MainCard Physical SIM, Due to which, the Hardware file cannot be processed in the SAP system (In case of SIM only New activation without MultiSIM, Correct SIM type is being sent in submit order request and No issue observed in HW file).

column41:
As we checked OGW is not handling additional VORAS status for ShipToStore orders scenarios

For Reference :
OS-74007 BUSINESS: CR: As a sales agent I want OGW to handle additional VORAS statusses after ShipToStore order - defect3

The requirements for a design gap in Device Financing Phase II.

It is regarding the use-case of ShipToStore and the if customer does not pick up the hardware in time and if the hardware is handed out afterwards, so far than the one documented, are sent from VORAS to OSF (OGW).OGW to handle these other statuses was not addressed during the design of device financing and is therefore not considered by OGW. 

OGW must be able to handle additional statuses coming from VORAS in case of ShipToStore use-case:

In case of scenario 5 (Follow on activities after Ship2Store order was not picked up by customer in time)  – OGW must handle other status updates than VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT once the record is recognized as Mailorder Ship2Store for the first time.

column1: OSF | ACC1 | Wave10.0 | Performance Defect | Response time degradation observed for Retrieve Customer Transaction
column41:
Observed response time degradation for Retrieve Customer transaction.
Steps to reproduce:
 # Launch ACC1 env.
 # Login
 # Customer Search
 # Retrieve Customer

[W10.0 OSF Performance Test Reports - VOIS - OSF - Vodafone Global Confluence|https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/display/OF/W10.0+OSF+Performance+Test+Reports+-+VOIS]
column324:
The identified performance defect in Wave 10.0 (Retrieve Customer Transaction) is causing significant response time degradation across critical customer-facing transactions in the ACC1 environment. These delays directly impact the end-user experience during high-volume operations.
If unresolved, these issues risk breaching SLAs for transaction processing and may delay the planned go-live for Wave 10.0, impacting both customer satisfaction and operational KPIs.

Hi [~simran.mogram1@vodafone.com] [~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com] 

We have reference to Wave 6.1:
*VFDED2W61S-145/ OS-6461* - {*}it is not our case{*}. We do not have ILS scenario here. *ProcessContext = ACQ* for both orders for both packages{*}. Thus, it is not an ILS!!!{*}
*VFDED2W61S-144/OS-6460* - I want to send Physical SIMs to SAP via OIL system - *seems to be our case*



First of all, I want to mention that packages are not totally identical and have differences inside the order.

Let me describe both provided cases. I have compared packages for each order

*OrderID 976877*

some differences are in blue

!image-2025-06-13-20-43-01-707.png!

*!image-2025-06-13-20-43-44-676.png!*

*Based on VFDED2W61S-144:*

*!image-2025-06-13-20-44-31-797.png!*

So, the first package does not have SIMCardType = S. Thus, taking into account user story description, MultiSimCount value is 0 and we should not create line '02' !!!

And vice versa for the second package: we have SIMCardType = S. Therefore we transfer '02' record to SAP.

 

We have almost the same case for the second order.

*OrderID 979485*

*the key difference is*

*!image-2025-06-13-20-45-21-301.png!*

*Let`s sum it up:*
*According to the [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/story.svg!VFDED2W61S-144: OMNIUS: SAP - As a Telesales Agent I want to send Physical SIMs to SAP via OIL system, so that SAP will do SIM card fulfilment.(OS-6460)Done|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED2W61S-144] ,* {*}application works as expected.{*}{*}{*};;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Incorrect CustomerOrderType value is being sent to OGW in submit order request for Mobile New Activation with ESIM Push scenario in Retail channel.
column41:
While performing Mobile Postpaid New Activation with ESIM push in Retail channel, We have observed that Omnius is sending incorrect CustomerOrderType value in submit order request.

Mobile New Activation with Hardware:
<UseCaseIndication>NACQMOB</UseCaseIndication>
<AttributeValue>WEC</AttributeValue>
 
Mobile New Activation without Hardware:
<UseCaseIndication>NACQMOB</UseCaseIndication>
<AttributeValue>TOH</AttributeValue>
 
Omnius screenshot:
 
!image-2025-06-10-14-05-23-288.png|width=406,height=104!

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
2. Create Mobile Postpaid package with Hardware or SIM only product.
3. Proceed to checkout and select ESIM with ESIM Push.
4. Generate contract and submit order.
5. Check submit order request logs.
 
Actual: Incorrect CustomerOrderType values is being sent to OGW in submit order request for Mobile New Activation with ESIM Push scenario in Retail channel.

Expected: Correct CustomerOrderType values should be sent to OGW in submit order request for Mobile New Activation with ESIM Push scenario in Retail channel.

i.e. expected values: if("HMK".equals(customerOrderType) || "POR".equals(customerOrderType)|| "RHW".equals(customerOrderType)) \{orderLineWithHardware = "true";}

As per the CR908 -> WEC & TOH values applicable only for D2C but currently Omnius is sending these values for New Activation without D2CWOC use cases.

!image-2025-06-10-14-04-08-744.png|width=474,height=63!

Reference ID: OAF-922 CR908 - Submit correct CustomerOrderType for D2C with owner change - Vodafone Global Jira

column875:
05/Jun/25 6:39 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;here is feedback from Portals Inciedent Meeting: 

Please provide more info:
 - why it should be a Portals Impact because so far only RNS, OM and OSF are involved?

+[~nina.pickl@vodafone.com] ;;;
column876:
06/Jun/25 5:36 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;[~anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com] , also VKD is involved, Unity can only communicate with OSF via VKD.

The flow is as follow:  cancellation reason ist trasferred from Unity vo VDK, afterwards VKD is trasferring the reason to OGW/OSF.

If OSF  is not getting the Info from VKD, the reason can not be displayed in OSF.

So the issue is between Unity and VKD and this change was already tested from your side. You can create a Defect against Unity, related to this test task: [[QA] OSF/VKD Gateway/Minerva Adapter - Adjustments Order Manager - Portals - Vodafone DE Confluence|https://de.confluence.agile.vodafone.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=599719049];;;
column877:
06/Jun/25 6:39 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;Ok. I'll double check it - maybe you're right. 

This feature is actually: [[DISPYRAMID-217] Adapt VKDGateway to pass through new order details - DE Jira|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/DISPYRAMID-217] should implement this.

Just for your understanding the root cause:

the cancellation as self seems to be working fine and this is working without Portals systems. RNS communicate in this case directly with OSF systems.

By displaying of information in OM the OSF accessing MinervaAdapter via VkdGateway. And here is probably the issue. I addressed it to team Pyramid as they implemented the extension for cancellation codes in April release 2025. 

 

 ;;;

column881:
13/Jun/25 12:10 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;*Update on PSTBUG*
*Ahmed ElZahaby, Vodafone (Team Pyramid) added a comment -*

I've looked in it, it seems like it's caused because the declined reason isn't founded in the enums that defined in StatusDetails in UnityOrderTracker, so the flow here we 've created an isCancellationReason:

https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/LUAAUTO/repos/unityordertracker/browse/UnityOrderTrackerScheduler/src/main/java/com/vodafone/cable/uotracker/updater/data/StatusDetail.java#254-256

That function checks if the order status that returned from MinervaAdaptor exists in CANCELLATION_REASON_MAP value and if it's not it set it with null:

https://webgit.kabeldeutschland.de/projects/LUAAUTO/repos/unityordertracker/browse/UnityOrderTrackerScheduler/src/main/java/com/vodafone/cable/uotracker/updater/vkdgateway/VkdGatewayOrderStatusUpdater.java?at=24d5d4b6d127bf5feee0bb99d80f3f74a73fc7df#63-66

And after I've search for the provided cancellation reason ''STORNO VORVERMARKTUNG'' ('CANCELLATION PRE-MARKETING') I didn't find it in the CANCELLATION_REASON_MAP values.

So, my suggested solution here if the team who is ever responsible for UnityOrderTracker just need to add that cancellation reason into the enums it has in StatusDetails.;;;

column886:
30/Jun/25 8:01 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;[~anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com]

We found the place in the VKD logs, where the cancellation reason=cancellation eventCode should be present, but it is missing.

Means the value of the Order Manager field "STATUS_DETAIL" is NOT present in the VKD Gateway logs for SOME cancellation reasons.

*Unity is not sending this code via Minera to VKD.* 

Like discussed in the beginning, someone from Cable team should create a Bug for Minerva and Unity team can check the cancellations reasons code table again.

The Unity change was implemented an year ago, maybe in the meantime some new cancellation reasons were added and they the table should now be updated.

 

VKD Log for the NOT working cancellation reason ‚Storno Vorvermarktung':

 

"statusInfos" : [#012    \{#012      "statusType" : "VALUE",#012      "system" : "cable",#012    "eventCode" : "CUSTOMER_ID",#012      "eventPresentationText" : "new cable customer id 173663507",#012      "eventValue" : "173663507"#012    }#  +*{color:#de350b}***MISSING PART***{color}*+

 

As example, for other reasons like 'double order', the value is present in the logs and it is also trasferregd from VKD to OSF, is working fine:

 

"statusInfos" : [#012    \{#012      "statusType" : "VALUE",#012      "system" : "cable",#012      "eventCode" : "CUSTOMER_ID",#012      "eventPresentationText" : "new cable customer id 566519401",#012      "eventValue" : "566519401"#012    },#012    {#012      "statusType" : "EVENT_DETAIL",#012      +{color:#00875a}*"eventCode" : "UXDU"#012*{color}+    }#012  ]#012};;;

Impact 
 # Duplicate Emails -> will not blocked, because VF-ID is working only on the code “200” and not on the status  
 # Invalid Emails -> will not blocked, because VF-ID is working only on the code “200” and not on the status  

In both scenarios we will create a VF-ID after the customer has confirmed the CS. 
For the first one Omnius will run in an error (see [OS-23802|https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOS-23802&data=05%7C02%7CAriadne.Thun1%40vodafone.com%7C53d99bb8392445a783fa08dda82d1344%7C68283f3b84874c86adb3a5228f18b893%7C0%7C0%7C638851633966437907%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=iOGREaLqo8PaBe3M2KN7EaISMu4B2WrVY67epTwQQQE%3D&reserved=0] ) and we will start the fulfillment without providing a VF-ID.

For the second one we will create a VF-ID for an email-address which is not allowed formally and might not run in an error by creation a VF-ID.

Both scenarios will be covered end of August with the error-handling epic.

select the KIP Product

column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1

Channel: Retail

PCAT version: V2500_2025_06_00_048

Test customer: 119045438 (MOB SOHO on address where KIP is available)

 

*Please note:*
 # because of the bug OS-73322 not possible to test this scenario on ACC2
 # For new-activation on ACC1 for MOB + KIP the field "Ausweisnummer (optional)" is not Read only

– > the field "Ausweisnummer (optional)" is Read only, it is not possible to enter anything

column569: Corrupt messages in “AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT” queue were causing the issue.
column874:
03/Jun/25 6:28 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Updates from TEMS Team:



TEMS received SBUS PR MQ curdepth alert for “AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT” queue by 8:30 AM CET. After receiving alert, we started troubleshooting the issue and below steps are done so far,

 
 # Firstly, we have checked SBUS logs and MQ logs and we have identified connectivity errors for AIR adapters in MQ logs.
 # We have restart http adapter along with SBUS MQ and listener and checked the status. All the channels were up but, still issue with HTTP adapter.
 # For analyzing, AIR adapter queue issue, we have checked AIR adapter MQ logs and Filesystem status, and we identified Filesystem was 100% utilized. We have done Filesystem cleanup and as well as extension with the help of VCI HP-UX Team and restarted AIR adapter MQs along with listeners.
 # We again took complete SBUS restart along with MQ and listener but still messages are not getting processed via HTTP queue and HTTP adapter is going in alarm state in GUI,

 
 # For further analysis, we approached to Development Team and they suggested to enable debug mode for SBUS logs. We have raised CCR INC000094087360 with Deployment Team to enable debug mode. After CCR implementation, we have restarted http adapter and extracted log files suggested by SBUS Development Team.
 # We have shared log files with Development Team and waiting for the analysis.;;;
column876:
03/Jun/25 8:55 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Updated from TEMS Team:



We had a call with SBUS Development Team and as per analysis, two corrupt messages in “AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT” queue were causing the issue.

 

Out of these two messages, first messages was Response call to the request, and it was quite old. During troubleshooting call, we were not able to identify why it was stuck in queue and as it was not trying to route to any other queue, we have deleted that message.

 

Second message type was “Message Type :4 (Report)” and this is not a normal behavior. So, for this issue Development Team suggested to raise SPN.

 

As suggested by Development Team, we have removed these messages and restarted HTTP adapter. All the messages are processed successfully,

 

_dis ql(AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT)_

    _51 : dis ql(AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT)_

_AMQ8409: Display Queue details._

   _QUEUE(AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT)             TYPE(QLOCAL)_

   _ACCTQ(QMGR)                             ALTDATE(2025-03-02)_

   _ALTTIME(05.18.43)_

   _BOQNAME(AAW.SBUSHTTP.SBUSOUT.BACKOUT)_

   _BOTHRESH(4)                             CLUSNL( )_

   _CLUSTER(FMCGRP)                         CLCHNAME( )_

   _CLWLPRTY(0)                             CLWLRANK(0)_

   _CLWLUSEQ(QMGR)                          CRDATE(2016-12-23)_

   _CRTIME(07.22.44)                        CURDEPTH(0)_

   _CUSTOM( )                               DEFBIND(NOTFIXED)_

   _DEFPRTY(0)                              DEFPSIST(NO)_;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Trusted flag Value as 'No' even if existing customer which is older than 6 months with DF tariffs
column41:
Hello

While performing Trusted flag Value as 'No' even if existing customer which is older than 6 months with DF tariffs

Test Data:

ILS: 969667

Steps To Reproduce:

1. Login to Telesales channel
2. Preform legacy search for S-BAN which is having a F-BAN
3. Load the customer
4. Verify Legacy Search should be successful
5. Perform change tariff
6. Add DF Tariff and HW
7. Move to Checkout
8. Fill all the required customer details
9. Submit the order
10. Verify in Process order and in submit order logs TrustedCustomerFlag as "Yes"


Actual Result: Trusted flag Value as 'No' even if existing customer which is older than 6 months with DF tariffs

Expected Result: Trusted flag Value should be 'Yes' even if existing customer which is older than 6 months with DF tariffs

Reference story: [OS-57791] OMNIUS_As a System I want to set the Trusted Customer flag value for a shopping cart, so that the flag details can be sent in SubmitOrder Request. [OS-57791] - Vodafone Global Jira
column324: Agent is not able to identify Trusted customer.
column569: InternalCreditClass was overwritten with the value of CollectionDelinquentStatus
column874:
02/Jun/25 8:27 AM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~anuradha.chougule@vodafone.com] 

 
Shruti Kanchan 
 
added a comment -
 
 
Can see BANCreation date is older than six months. However there was an improvement in TrustedCustomerFlag in OS-63733 to update the calculation based on
 # If the {{BANCreationDate}} is 6 months or older (as per the logic in OS-57791),

 # *AND* {{CollectionDelinquentStatus}} is “N”

 # *AND* {{InternalCreditClass}} is >=1 and

 # *AND* InternalCreditClass is <=2

 # *THEN* set {{TrustedFlag}} = *Yes* in the SubmitOrder request sent to OGW.

In the getCustomerDetail Mode 1 response of the sample attached, I can see that InternalCreditClass = N, which is not a valid value; it has to be a numeric value, anything apart from that will impact the trusted customer flag to be set as N

!5d00d450-1cbd-495c-a553-fb2eaaec3a1d.png!

Kshitij Kumar Srivastava 
 
added a comment -
 
 
Hi Ajay,

Customer Password inputfield over UI shown for MOB and DSL customers only. (not for cable)
in following usecases i..e 
MOB : ACQ, X-sell with new BAN. D2C,
DSL : ACQ, MOVE
Introduced in wave-3 ref [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/story.svg!VFDED1W3S-1958: Customer Password (‘Kundenkennwort’) Checkout DROP 1Done|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1W3S-1958]

 

basically captured password not to shown over checkout summary section (before submit)
as it is always in masked over UI and also not add any value to show in masked format.

*Addition* : captured password shown over Order details view (after submit).
where this can be shown either masked or unmasked format based on permission (UNCOVER_PASSWORD)






*Conclusion* : 

Captured password must not shown over checkout summary section (before submit)
It shown over Order details view (after submit).
where this can be shown either masked or unmasked format based on permission (UNCOVER_PASSWORD)

 

Could you please check and update on this;;;

THis is a requirement or a design gap on telesales DSL password summary in telesales because on Telesales Mobile has Ident Method the password is seen in summary Kundenidentifikation

column889:
18/Jun/25 12:19 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;As per yesterday's call we had the below things which were done and tried to investigate the scenarios
1.  Defect was retested by testing team and issue was reproduced
2. Amdocs DBA analyzed and debugged the issue where SQL queries were checked and as per DBA they did not identified any issue in SQL statement checks
3. Post Amdocs Dev Analysis it was identified that issue might be due to Media type where only Media type = NT was accepted by the Activation Daemon but media type PA was rejected and what we observed was that the orders from KIAS test team which were directly placed by CSM team had Media type NT but the orders which were placed from OSF had media type PA.
4. Post the above analysis KIAS dev and VF team decided to provide a new Binary file for extra logs debugging which was placed locally in the VF server bin directory and then KIAS was restarted.
5. New flow was triggered and it worked -- but this doesn't seem to be a permanent fix as temporary the orders are flowing and passed but this issue can still occur and not yet fully resolved 

Please do find the overall comments and analysis from Amdocs and VF 
In the last call I was with Andreas Knocke(VF) and Christina(VF) and we agreed that Amdocs check whether there is any dependency on Media Category and Andreas(VF) will approach the OCI Oracle team again. 
As per Amdocs result: There is NO dependency. 
 
In the call with the DBAs yesterday, testers ran the flow but DBAs were not able to see any session. 
The problem seems to be a synchronization issue between the nodes of the distributed database in OCI. This can only be resolved by Vodafone, by the team that managers the OCI cloud DBs. 
 ;;;

column41:
While performing BEW retail scenario, we observed that BEW Erfassen is enabled even if BEW version updated.

*Test data* - 
Customer -103445706

*Steps to Reproduce -*

1.Login to Retail channel as FI agent
2. Search existing mobile customer with ADV and DEV version less than 4
3. Retrieve the customer and click on BEW Bearbeiten button
4. Verify BEW banner notification
5. Select BEW ERFASSEN
6. Select checkbox for ADV/DEV
7. Click on "Dokument erstellen"(Create document) button
8. Document will be generated
9. Post that search the customer again
10. Select BEW Bearbeiten button
11. Verify BEW Erfassen button.

*Actual Result -* Post updating the version BEW Erfassen button is enabled.

*Expected Result -* Post updating the version BEW Erfassen button should be disabled.

column888:
02/Jun/25 1:02 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~akash.ubbu@vodafone.com] [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] 

Shival Gupta

added a comment -

Hi Akash/Ari,

If OS-12220 is ON, and Error Handling Switch is OFF,

 Then Omnius will display warning message only if Response Code is other than 200.

In this case, the response is with Code 200. Therefore, Omnius considers it successful, and there will not be any error message. (Refer to OS-28389 and OS-24967)

 If an error is expected here, then Response Code must be other than 200.

 

Further error handling within Response Code 200 is part of OS-23334 (Epic Error Handling).;;;

03/Jun/25 1:22 PM;akash.ubbu@vodafone.com;Hi Everyone,

Now issue is resolved, error is showing for Duplicate email now.

!image-2025-06-03-13-19-36-603.png|width=427,height=152!

 

We needed to change the following endpoint in acc1:

Service Settings -> DXL Settings -> Contact Medium Validation url

 

FROM:                 /osf/v1/emailValidation

TO:                       /osf/v1/tmf-api/digitalIdentityManagement/v4/contactMediumValidation

 

As mentioned in User story [OS-61399] OMNIUS_OSE_As Omnius, I want to add configurable parameter as ON/OFF switch so that I can decide whether the functionalities defined in this Epic need to be enabled or disabled based on parameter value (OS-61399) - Vodafone Global Jira

 
 * Omnius will check the parameter value set in Omnius AdminUI (Backoffice) for *"VFID Error Handling Switch* *"* and take following action based on parameter value.
 * If the configuration parameter indicates that the *"VFID Error Handling Switch"* is enabled (value of parameter = {_}"Yes"{_}), Omnius will enable all the Epic functionalities defined in [OS-28388|https://eur03.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOS-28388&data=05%7C02%7Cakash.ubbu%40vodafone.com%7Ca8f0a9b0a08b401a5c9008dda26f6f44%7C68283f3b84874c86adb3a5228f18b893%7C0%7C0%7C638845321753373264%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=%2B7vhHW8TlFmTUvEGgFWdPuTDCBZQcgsAey4HZrAwbbA%3D&reserved=0]:
 * Else (configuration does not exists or value = {_}"No"{_}), Omnius will disable all the functionalities and proceed with BAU.


 * Directly after the initial deployment, the switch will be set as "No" (Default value). Later on, it will be considered as the last saved status value.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Subscriber Number is missing in submit order request for Mobile Retail channel.
column41:
While performing Mobile Postpaid New Activation in the Retail channel. We have observed that the Subscriber Number is missing in the submit order request fulfillment mode. This is causing KIAS to create a new subscriber number for customer activation, which leads to different subscriber numbers being present in the contract document and KIAS. OGW receives the subscriber number in the AllocateBanAndCtnNumber response from KIAS and passes the same to Omnius in the submit order response and that subscriber number should be sent to OGW from Omnius for order fulfillment in submit order fulfillment mode to activated customer on the same subscriber number. However, due to the missing subscriber number in the submit order request, KIAS assigns a different subscriber number for order fulfillment which resulting in a mismatch between the subscriber number in the contract document and the one used for customer activation.

This issue is working fine in ACC2 Production branch Env - v9.21.12-BB42

Please find below details:

*ACC1 Submit Order Request: Fulfillment Mode*

<SubscriberList>
<SubscriberDetails>
<SourceSubscriberID>1</SourceSubscriberID>
{color:#de350b}*<SubscriberNumber/>*{color}
<SourceCustomerID>1</SourceCustomerID>
<AddressSequenceList>1</AddressSequenceList>
<AddressSequenceList>3</AddressSequenceList>
<AddressSequenceList>4</AddressSequenceList>
<AddressSequenceList>5</AddressSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>1</ContactSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>2</ContactSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>3</ContactSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>4</ContactSequenceList>
<SystemAdditionalData>
<SystemName>KIAS</SystemName>
<AttributeCode>NewSerialNumber</AttributeCode>
<AttributeValue>89155014908049</AttributeValue>
</SystemAdditionalData>
</SubscriberDetails>
</SubscriberList>

*ACC2 Submit Order Request: Fulfillment Mode*

SubscriberList>
<SubscriberDetails>
<SourceSubscriberID>1</SourceSubscriberID>
{color:#00875a}*<SubscriberNumber>1723902862</SubscriberNumber>*{color}
<SourceCustomerID>1</SourceCustomerID>
<AddressSequenceList>1</AddressSequenceList>
<AddressSequenceList>2</AddressSequenceList>
<AddressSequenceList>3</AddressSequenceList>
<AddressSequenceList>4</AddressSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>1</ContactSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>2</ContactSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>3</ContactSequenceList>
<ContactSequenceList>4</ContactSequenceList>
<SystemAdditionalData>
<SystemName>KIAS</SystemName>
<AttributeCode>NewSerialNumber</AttributeCode>
<AttributeValue>89155014613789</AttributeValue>
</SystemAdditionalData>
</SubscriberDetails>
</SubscriberList>

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Create Mobile Postpaid Package.
 # Proceed to checkout and submit order.
 # Verify submit order fulfillment request.

Actual: Subscriber Number is missing in submit order request for Mobile Retail channel.

Expected: Subscriber Number should be sent in submit order request for Mobile Retail channel.

Note: Please find attached logs for ACC1 & ACC2 Environments.

SunilkumarCM 
 
Jadded a comment 
 
Hi Srujana,
 
I checked further on ACC1 due to cable artifact config issue we were not able to reproduce on ACC1 and later after changing configuration now we have validate address issue 

But based on further analysis with info like serviceability we see it is not an issue and expected behavior when we have below the serviceability meet below criteria.

!24021afa-4c1b-40cc-a0d8-49d48cd9119e.png!
h3. Expected Behavior

*Valid for cable TV package*

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = J
technician_needed_yes  = 1V1 / {*}VP0{*}/ TECYESTV chargeable product should not be added in SC.

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = N - Remain as is (existing behaviour)
technician_needed_no - default = TECNOTV
technician_needed_yes - manual = 1V1 / {*}VP0{*}/ TECYESTV 

 

*Valid for KIP package*

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = J
technician_needed_yes - default and readonly = TECYESKIP chargeable product should not added in SC
technician_needed_no - not possbile as dropdown is freez

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y *AND* *ABK* = N - Remain as is (existing behaviour)
technician_needed_no - default = TECNOKIP
technician_needed_yes -  not to show in Dropdown

*selbstInstallationKz* = N AND *ABK* = N - Remain as is (existing behaviour)
technician_needed_yes - default = TECYESKIP
technician_needed_no -  not to show in Dropdown

 

According to this info we can see in check serviceability bar that

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = N for the address so we show Self installation block

 ;;;

We are performing new activation for VUM retail order and found request received by Antpoint/Minerva doesn’t contain the new <permissionEvidenceIdentification> field in the OGW logs.

Test Data

VUM retail= 967873
Web order id=6231933


Steps to reproduce:

1. Login to Retail
2. Add KIP Package
3. Select tariff and hardware
4. Fill required details
5. Submit Order
6. Complete the backend process.




*Actual Result :* =  For VUM retail order request received by Antpoint/Minerva doesn’t contain the new <permissionEvidenceIdentification> field in the OGW logs.

*Expected Result* = for VUM retail order  request received by Antpoint/Minerva should contain the new <permissionEvidenceIdentification> field in the OGW logs.
column324: In the OGW logs <permissionEvidenceIdentification> field is missing due to which validation cannot be done.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Regression | Incorrect masking format showing on SPIN authentication window
column41:
While Authenticating customer using MTAN and SPIN MOB and SPIN CAB authentication incorrect masking format is showing on authentication window 

 

Steps to Reproduce 

1) Login Telesales/retail channel

2) Disabled soft authentication from backend 

3) Perform index/legacy customer search

4) Customer retrieved in masking format

5) Click on customer details

6) Incorrect masking format is observed

 

Customer ID: *118012286* 

Actual Result: 

!image-2025-05-26-18-17-03-640.png!

 

Expected Result:  

 

!image-2025-05-26-18-16-41-286.png!
column324: Customer Can be authenticated but incorrect masking format can cause Security problem
column569: RCA: The issue arose because the same masking logic was used for both phone numbers and IBANs. With the new CR883 implementation, the logic for IBAN masking was updated, inadvertently altering the phone number masking as well. This caused discrepancies in data handling

column41:

While performing mobile Customer search omnius is not showing loan details after clicking on  “Device Financing" tab 

Test data:

1.Agent should remove permission "BOOK_DF_TARIFFS_WITH_HARDWARE" from back office.
2.Existing DF customer should be available

1.Login to Omnius as Telelsales/Retail channel.
2.Search Existing Mobile customer.
3.Verify Customer search result on search result page.
4.Click on DF arrow and Check Device Financing Tab on subscriber level

column882:
29/May/25 1:34 PM;simran.mogram1@vodafone.com;As discussed with [~shruti.kanchan@vodafone.com] 
Condition 1: device_financing_duration value is greater than > initial_period value of Tariff
Then Infotext should be : " Summe bei Kündigung des Mobilfunkvertrags n. Mindestlaufzeit " ("Amount upon termination of the mobile phone contract after the minimum term")
OR If InfoText1 is not sent then Omnius must use \{InfoText2 } I.e 
"Summe bei Fortsetzung des Mobilfunkvertrags n. Mindestlaufzeit" ("Amount upon continuation of the mobile phone contract after the minimum term"). Infotext2 should be printed once. It was concluded that this is a design gap. Omnius to raise a CR to change the logic for sending Infotext 2 (defined inOS-61667) only for LinePayment = REC which has no EndPeriod (or no Sliding_Calculator).
 

Defect ll be open for tracking purpose.
