column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1/PR | DSL /FTTH Phase3 order is going to fulfillment started status after completed success again
column41:
While performing below scenario, we have observed that DSL /FTTH order is going to fulfillment started status after completed success again

*Observations:*
 # *Order is going to fullfillment started status after completed success again.(Order is not success)*

There is only 1 second difference between ORDER_POSITION_COMPLETE(1286) and ORDER_COMPLETED(1290) *if we are processing order next day*

And {*}OGW is processing ORDER_COMPLETED earlier than ORDER_POSITION_COMPLETE{*}, and hence order goes to fullfillment started status again

Test data: Omnius: 966097 , Barcode: VDE7700008354

!image-2025-05-22-20-19-50-968.png!

*Test Data:*

Test data: FTTH order Omnius: 1092837, Barcode: VDE5602849604

OGW Order id :2849604

*Env* – PR/ ACC1

 

*Step to reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius with Telesales/Retail channel

2)Configure DSL/FTTH Phase3 Package

3)Submit order

4)Check order status after COM database

6)Verify InProgress-FulfillmentStarted after Completed-Success

*Actual Result:* OGW showing Push Order Status as InProgress-FulfillmentStarted after Completed-Success 

*Expected Result:* OGW should show Push Order Status as Completed-Success for FTTH Phase2 orders

Please find ref defect:

[https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-59580]
column324: DSL and FTTH PHASE2 ACT Flow impacted due to this issue -Orders are not reached to completed (success) status
column569: CR553 is off, current implementation is the old logic
column874:
23/May/25 12:39 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

OGW got 3 sos request at the same second: 1 completed success, 2 customer created
currently we reverted the kafka solution that was supposed to handle issues like this.

in the current logic OGW will not wait until the process of handling 1 sos is finished
we are handling all 3 requests simultaneously.
!image-2025-05-23-10-08-04-763.png!

 

so if there will not be some buffer of more then a few milliseconds this issue can occur again;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | Epic PHP Upgrade 8.1 | ACC1 | Test2B | Cable & UM | Getting "Request failed with status code: 503 Backend fetch failed" error while performing add KIP package(New Activation) & change package(ILS) flow
column41:
We observed that while performing add KIP package & change package flows, getting error as *"Request 'configurator/cart/getRules' failed with status code: 503 Backend fetch failed".*

*Steps to Reproduce -*
1.Login into omnius via telesales/retail agent
2. Perform serviceability for new activation
3. Add KIP package 
4. Verify error message on configurator.

*Actual Result -* "Request 'configurator/cart/getRules' failed with status code: 503 Backend fetch failed" error message is displayed on configurator for new activation.

*Expected Result -* Error message should not be displayed on configurator for new activation.

*NOTE* - The same issue is observed for normal ILS flow.

 ;;;
column880:
23/May/25 6:19 PM;nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com;Hello

Output from the meeting

Thank you for participating and especially to Nasir and Andreas for analysing the test results during the call.
Unfortunately Amdocs could not participate, so we need a confirmation from Gaurab that our investigation result is correct

Results:
It looks like a Defect in the OGW software:
After the GetMFBan request from OGW to EAI->KIAS
-EAI hands over the F-BAN parameter to OGW
-OGW maps the parameter (so.. no XSD version issue between OGW and EAI)
-OGW does not hand over the F-BAN parameter as part of the GetCustomerDetails response

AccTesting Ticket has been sent to Amdocs:
OS-73161] OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Omnius is not sending GFP call for existing customer of device financing - Vodafone Global Jira
It includes the test logfiles from OGW/EAI

TODO: Amdocs (please until Monday 12:00 CET) :
-confirm that indeed it is accepted as an OGW defect
-deliver expected delivery date for fix

@Gaurab Mitra
In case of any questions, please call nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com, because he has performed the tests and has direct access to the logfiles on the test environment.
If another meeting is needed, please invite for Monday morning or ask me to do that

THANK YOU!!;;;

column881:
23/May/25 5:44 PM;nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com;Hello 

Output from the meeting

Thank you for participating and especially to Nasir and Andreas for analysing the test results during the call.
Unfortunately Amdocs could not participate, so we need a confirmation from Gaurab(?) that our investigation result is correct

Results:
It looks like a Defect in the OGW software: 
After the GetMFBan request from OGW to EAI->KIAS
-EAI hands over the F-BAN parameter to OGW
-OGW maps the parameter (so.. no XSD version issue between OGW and EAI)
-OGW does not hand over the F-BAN parameter as part of the GetCustomerDetails response

AccTesting Ticket has been sent to Amdocs:
OS-73161] OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Omnius is not sending GFP call for existing customer of device financing - Vodafone Global Jira
It includes the test logfiles from OGW/EAI 

TODO: Amdocs (please until Monday 12:00 CET) :  
-confirm that indeed it is accepted as an OGW defect
-deliver expected delivery date for fix

@Gaurab Mitra
In case of any questions, please call nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com, because he has performed the tests and has direct access to the logfiles on the test environment.
If another meeting is needed, please invite for Monday morning or ask me to do that


THANK YOU!!

;;;
column882:
23/May/25 6:00 PM;nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com;As analyzed from meeting

After the GetMFBan request from OGW to EAI->KIAS
-EAI hands over the F-BAN parameter to OGW
-OGW maps the parameter (so.. no XSD version issue between OGW and EAI)
-OGW does not hand over the F-BAN parameter as part of the GetCustomerDetails response

Hence issue is assigned to OGW.

Please find attached GetMFCustomerBAN request and response.

 !image-2025-05-23-18-03-45-885.png|thumbnail!

column913:
02/Jul/25 3:35 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;This problem seems to exist for longer and in different forms, for example this one from 2024: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OSIP-1486 

[~joerg.trierweiler1@vodafone.com] investigated it and it seems like the problem is the following:
 * there are different places where a SOHO customer can enter a company name: in the customer details, the delivery options, the billing address
 * for a new customer order, the OSF frontend only forces the agent to enter the company name in the customer details; but if additional billing address or delivery options are given, the frontend makes it optional to enter the company name
 ** however, when such an order is send, OrderGateway creates a SkyForce ticket because the company name is missing => OSF frontend thinks the company name is optional, OGW seems to think it is mandatory
 * for existing customers the problem seems to be worse, because loading a SOHO customer pre-enters the company name in the customer details, but not for the other fields. 
 ** even if no deviating delivery address is chosen, OGW deems it mandatory and refuses the order

These orders do not arrive in VkdGateway, so the cable side never actually gets to see this. We do not understand how the validation in OrderGateway works, so we need TechM to investigate this further.

In ECC, the company name is also mandatory, but here the frontend supports that validation and does not allow you to actually check out and generate a wrong order.

I currently am not sure if there are additional validations down the line in the cable stack that would act up, too, when the company name is missing. We are in contact with colleagues about this.

But the problem at hand seems to stem from OrderGateway and cable has no way to investigate this much deeper.

We would need to know:
 * what validations for the company name existing OrderGateway
 * or more specifically for the case at hand: why are these order failing when placing an order for a new customer with additional delivery details? (as described in this bug);;;

18/Jul/25 2:14 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] 

Do you think it would be possible to talk to a TechM colleague directly? I feel like this is going back and forth without any progress.

We are very certain that this is not a a VkdGateway behaviour, because in our logs, this order does not even arrive. Also, our systems don't have a validation for a mandatory company name, and the nomenclature COMPANY_NAME isn't used by us at all.

Also, the Sky-Tickets are not created by us, but by OSF. It may usually be a reaction of OSF to VkdGateway refusing an order – I cannot judge that, I cannot see OSF code. But then, it would be very nice if they could tell us what VkdGateway call supposedly refuses that order. Since they are writing the Sky tickets, they should be able to see that.

column927:
18/Jul/25 8:07 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] , 

yes, exactly. From the digging we did, we did not find any validation that checks for the company name being present. Also, the phrase "COMPANY_NAME" written as it is is something we do not use. I would hope that the colleagues from OSF could find in their code when the "Required Input COMPANY_NAME missing" error is constructed and written into the OGWERR-1408.

For us, it is completely intransparent how this error comes to be.

OSF and/or OrderGateway take these deliveryDetails entered in the frontend, and we could imagine that there is some validation in OrderGateway itself that causes the problem (but we can't know for sure). [~natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com]  mentioned that a Sky-Ticket by OSF is usually created only when the cable systems refuse the order. I guess this would need to be the *orderNewCustomer* endpoint of VkdGateway, but we do not receive any calls on that endpoint in these cases. If this is in fact a reaction of OSF to some refusal by the cable systems, it would be very helpful to know what call OSF/OrderGateway is doing and what the response is from VkdGateway that causes OSF to write Sky-Ticket.

I hope communication is easier when we can directly talk to the colleagues, because the communication over this ticket seems to be very not ideal anymore.

 

(Regarding validations in our systems: the only validation that we have in regards of these customer addresses is that the deliveryDetails and billingInformation etc. – so all these extra customer details – must either all be for a private person or all be for a legal person (SOHO), but never mixed.  So, currently, we do not allow that a SOHO customer (customerPersonType = "SOH") enters a private address (deliveryPersonType="KUN").

But I am not aware of any cases where this caused problems yet in the communication with OSF – which might only be me being uninformed of course.);;;

Die folgenden Produkte: [KCO4SD1060] Vodafone Cover Plus (mit Diebstahlschutz) 5,99 EUR können nicht hinzugefügt werden weil sie mit der aktuellen Auswahl nicht kombinierbar sind.

column883:
05/Jun/25 5:42 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;We are efacing here the results of two contradicting user stories:
 * CR650/FAST-719 Disallow VF Cover Plus Handset insurance for SOHO costumers
 * OAF-750/OPLM-6629: Consider COVER PLUS insurance product for Vodafone Black tariffs - Categories & Rules

added a comment -
 
 
Hello Krishnkumar,

 
 # 2OFX permission is necessary as per business 

 # If 2OFX permission is not assigned & SPIN_CAB is failed then red banner with no 2ofx window is seen 

 # If SPIN getpartial verification response code is 400 then Message: "SPIN authentication not possible (technical error)"  is expected
[!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/story.svg!VFDED2W81S-25: OMNIUS_As a system I want to check the response for DXL Get call, so that I can proceed for DXL Partial-Authentication call or redirect to 3/4 authentication method [OS-28489]Done|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED2W81S-25] - GETPARTIAL VERFICATION SPIN original story 
[!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/story.svg!VFDED2W81S-30: OMNIUS_CUST : As a system I want to validate the response code from the DXL POST request, so that I can proceed with SPIN Authentication or redirect to 3/4 authentication method [OS-28497]Done|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED2W81S-30] - POSTPARTIAL VERFICATION SPIN original story 

*Getstatus :200*  see radio button with cable ID & click on authenticate button 
after clicking authenticate button ;
*getpartialverification is triggered* ( if response is 200, we see index box to enter PIN input. else based on different response codes 400, 409 , 500, 503 we get different red banner message) as per Harmonize authentication if SPIN_CAB fails we see 2ofx window to authenticate.({*}Here we are getting 400 as per logs){*}

if *getpartialverification response is 200* & index input pin are entered then *postpartialverification is triggered if this response is 200* then spin_Cab auth passes ( if again postpartialverification response is 400, 409, 500, 503 we see different red bannner with next auth method 2OFX_AUTH to authenticate. 

 

*This is working as expected as per logs, please have agent assigned 2ofx permission to be able to see further 3/4 authentication in case spin cable failing.*;;;
column880:
19/May/25 1:22 PM;krishnkumar.satpute@vodafone.com;Hi,

We checked with and without the 20FX permission in BO, and the same error appears in both cases.

!image-2025-05-19-13-10-37-585.png|width=400,height=212!

OAF-810 Part -3 : OMNIUS, CUST : As an Agent, i wanted to authenticate via service pin cable in harmonized way, so that if spin_cab fails, system offer next authentication method in harmonized manner. - Vodafone Global Jira

OAF-798 Part -3 : OMNIUS, CUST : As an Agent, I wanted to retrieve possible authentication method from system based on customer and agent, so that system perform hard authentication in harmonized manner. - Vodafone Global Jira

As per Above user story, assigning SPIN_CAB should show the SPIN_CAB window first. The error (Customer can't be authenticated at the moment due to no authentication method available) should only appear if it's skipped and no permission is set. So, the SPIN_CAB window should not depend on the 20FX permission.

 

Please let us know if we missed anything.

 ;;;

14/May/25 6:39 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;as per the latest findings it seems that might be someone from Nestor team is updating the Minerva URL at backend which might cause interruption for customer search.
ACC1-->Test2b-->UAT06 was agreed and connected since 24.03.2025 but today we observed that Test2b flows were moving sometimes to UAT05 and UAT06 which caused interruptions

Checking with Nestor team for the same:-
Hello Nestor, could you please check if the Minerva/Cama configuration for test2b is being overwritten by anything? Yesterday and earlier today i saw the correct configuration (MinervaUAT). However currently i see that according to the endpoint report /minerva is wrongly configured now: 
.
 
Since end of March we should have the following VF West endpoints configured: 
I think this is causing issues for OSF with their orders ending up in the wrong VF West environment. 
Thus can you please look into it and correct the configuration? ;;;

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Device financing Total and Monthly Amount format is not generated correctly in Hardware file.
column41:

Order id: 961767

SAP expects the final amount and the monthly rate in Cent (as for HWI amount).

Current values: |558|46.5

SAP expects: |55800|4650|12^

{*}Reference Story{*}: OS-61322

{*}Steps to Reproduce{*}:

1) Login to Telesales
2) Perform New activation Mobile
3) Configure mobile package with DF tariff and HW
3) Submit order
4) HW file generated

{*}Actual Result{*}: Device financing Total and Monthly Amount format is not generated correctly in Hardware file.

{*}Expected Result{*}: Device financing Total and Monthly Amount format should be correctly in Hardware file.

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | VORAS-UAT01 | Set order status not receive from VORAS for Mobile Retail orders.
column41:
We are performing new activation for Mobile retail order and found after completion of Mobile order in VORAS setOrderStatus response is not received in OGW. 
Test Data

Mobile retail= 961435,961727


Steps to reproduce:

1. Login to Retail
2. Add Mobile Package
3. Select tariff and hardware
4. Fill required details
5. Submit Order
6. Once you received status OnHold-Pending-POS-HWFulfillment
7. Send the mail for VORAS



*Actual Result :* = After completion of Mobile order in VORAS setOrderStatus response is not received in OGW.
*Expected Result* =After completion of Mobile order in VORAS setOrderStatus response should be received in OGW.

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Web and Script Server cache is not clearing as expected when the OSE delivery includes a JS fix.
column41:
This is tracking defect for cleanup js cache post deployment.

As discussed, we had a code fix on the script server (JS file) as part of the delivery, but the fix did not work in ACC on the same day of deployment. When we tested the same ticket the next day after the automatic import and publish, everything worked perfectly fine.

Additionally, we have observed that the "OS-72625 Ticket" started working as expected after the automatic PCAT import and publish. This seems to indicate that whenever we implement a JavaScript fix, the functionality does not work as expected on the same day due to cache issue.

Could you please check if there are any additional jobs or scripts utilized to clear the cache after the automatic publish, It would be helpful if you could provide a script to the deployment team to clear all caches, including both web and script server caches. This would help us to test urgent fixes on the same day instead of having to wait until the next day.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | CR869 | ACC1 | Unity | In Move from VKD to VUM within same area code ,"Anzahl der zu übernehmenden Rufnummern" section is showing as "Keine Rufnummern"
column41:
In Move from VUM to VKD within same area code ,"Anzahl der zu übernehmenden Rufnummern" section is showing as "Keine Rufnummern"

*Steps to Recreate:*

Take a UM Customer in ULM Region (CN:408100401)

Perform Move to VKD Address with in same area code(Address:Wallstraße 9, 89231 Neu-Ulm )

Check the porting section field "Anzahl der zu übernehmenden Rufnummern: should be in {color:#ff8b00}accordance with the telephone numbers of the former VUM-contract. {color}

{color:#ff8b00}But Intstead the section is showing as Keine Rufnummern{color}

 

*Expected Results:* The section "Rufnummernubernahme" field   "Anzahl der zu übernehmenden Rufnummern" value should be shown with the VUM Contract telephone numbers

(Attaching the screenshots)

*Actual Result:* Under the Porting section "Rufnummernubernahme" field showing as "Kein Rufnummern"

column1: OSF | Wave 10 | ACC1 | Retail | New "TAN Entry field" not available in OSF frontend portal
column41:
TAN code field not available in OSF front end portal before generating the document screen.

*Steps to Reproduce:*

    1. Login to Omnius using Retail Channel ACC1 Environment
    2. Check if ALLOW_EMAIL_VERIFICATION_TEMP is ON
    3. Perform Serviceability address check for Cable UM address
    4. Verify if the customer type selected is private only
    5. Select Cable UM package from add package section
    6. Fill in the customer firstname, lastname, DOB and other required details.
    *7.* *Check if the weiter button & Verifizierung starten button is disabled*
    *8. Enter a valid customer email address*

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | Omnius is allowing agents to modify the checkout section data even after the Generate Contract mode has been generated for Prepaid in the Telesales channel.
column41:
While performing Mobile Prepaid New Activation in Telesales channel, We have observed, Omnius is allowing agents to modify the checkout section data even after the Generate Contract mode has been generated due to which different data is being sent in submit order request.

!image-2025-05-05-15-15-38-358.png|width=522,height=274!

!image-2025-05-05-15-16-10-388.png|width=522,height=274!

!image-2025-05-05-15-16-37-458.png|width=523,height=275!

!image-2025-05-05-15-17-59-347.png|width=524,height=249!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Mobile Prepaid package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Clicks on Vertragszusammenfassung senden button.
 # Generate contract mode trigger.
 # Omnius received Generate contract mode response and proceed to next section.
 # Omnius allows agent to modify checkout section even after going to next section (Weiter/Voicelog).

Actual: Omnius is allowing agents to modify the checkout section data even after the Generate Contract mode has been generated for Prepaid in the Telesales channel.

Expected: Omnius should not allow agents to modify the checkout section data if the Generate Contract mode has been generated for Prepaid in the Telesales channel.

Note: [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] This issue is reproducible on Production branch as well.
column324: Different data will be sent in fulfillment mode for customer fulfillment.
column569: No Change required.
column874: 06/May/25 4:33 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] is trying to reproduce this issue, will update after further progress;;;
column875:
07/May/25 10:33 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Divya Kumbla added a comment - 
 
 
[~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com]  For prepaid orders we don’t send contract to the customer ,please check the generate contract response .And before submit we can still modify the data of the customer.;;;
column876:
07/May/25 11:12 AM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Hi [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] 
Yes, for prepaid we don't have contract summary but if agent has submitted order (Generate contract mode - submit order trigger) then Omnius should not allow agent to change anything in checkout without refreshing page, Can you please check with [~kshitij.srivastava2@vodafone.com]  :);;;
column877:
08/May/25 8:21 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Kshitij Kumar Srivastava added a comment -
 
 
[~ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com] 

 

This is an standard/generic behaviour in Omnius before SubmitOrder(fulfilment) service call, agent can go back and edit anything.
And until SubmitOrder(fulfilment) service call, shoppingcart+checkout data consider as offer in Omnius.

There is not such restriction in Omnius for prepaid package/order after SubmitOrder (generateContract) to go back in sales flow and edit sc or checkout.

So this is not a valid.

Also refer ; OAF-530.;;;
column878: 08/May/25 9:20 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Thank you [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] [~kshitij.srivastava2@vodafone.com] !!;;;

column324: OGW is unable to identify for which order package they need to update the response. As a result, they are updating the response for both packages due to which Postpaid order details are shown in Prepaid package - Irrelevant information shown in prepaid package.
column569:
There is no possibility to switch this handling of Error completely to order line level, as for Multiorder there are activities which takes place on Order and BAN level at first and only if this is successful the processing on order line and Subscriber level starts. Theoretically the error handling of processing on order line / Subscriber level starts could be “improve”.

As confirmed by VF KIAS BA, Closing this ticket with WAD.

column324: Unable to authenticate Mobile customer with SPIN as we do not know the SPIN. Usually we get the SPIN via SOAPUI request, and can use it for authentication then.
column569: There was a Change that for MOB the Activation Code was introduced. Get_SPIN_MOB can only be done if there is an existing and active Activation Code. Fixed on DXL side. It is possible to create an Activation Code via SoapUI
column874: 05/May/25 6:19 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Hello [~raniero.calzavara@vodafone.com], could you please check this ticket on your side;;;
column876:
07/May/25 1:20 PM;raniero.calzavara@vodafone.com;This is not a DXL bug.

Due to a security requirement the GET /pin functionality for mobile customers was disabled.

If you need to get the pin for mobile customers using the DXL testservicepin API, a new flow must be defined.

Please define the requirements together with the DXL system designers, you can get in touch with [johannes.teutrine1@vodafone.com|mailto:johannes.teutrine1@vodafone.com] to define the next steps.;;;
column877:

15/May/25 12:13 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added  a comment - 
 
 
 
Hi 

I discussed further with @Bas Smeets found that the issue is because of Files from cable_artifact.phar/vendor folder which are running on PSR/LOG-1.1.0 version are trying to refer the dependencies of OSE/vendor folder having PSR/LOG-3.0.0 version. This version mismatch is causing the issue.

To solve the same we either need to work on how we load or manage dependencies of OSE / InstallBase API & the Cable Artifact.

or we need to convey the challenges we have and ask the Cable artifact team to upgrade the PSR/LOG version to latest >= 3.0.0

 

Thanks;;;
column893: 15/May/25 1:59 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Checking the POCs from Cable artifact team, will schedule call according to availability;;;
column894:
15/May/25 5:00 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;*OSF | Wave10.0 | Checkpoint | DM | OS-72560 | ACC1 | MoM and Action items (15th May, 2025)*
 
As discussed in call,
 - As per Sven Rautenberg, TechM Code is using 2 different versions of same software
 - Also there are multiple LoggerInterface files & the Autoloading is somehow using whichever may be latest
 - We need codebase which can support both PHP version 7 & 8
 - Sunil will try to downgrade psr log file and check if it works
 - If doesn't work, will have to ask Cable Artifact team to upgrade it
 ;;;
column895:
15/May/25 5:49 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Comment from Sunil over mail : 

Hi team,
 
We checked further and found that downgrading the PSR/LOG is not an easy option as InstallBaseAPI built on Luman framework is of version 10, which uses package "monolog/monolog", intern this package is expecting at least "psr/log": "^2.0 || ^3.0" version.
So conclusion is Downgrade is possible only on our OSE S/W but not on InstallBaseAPI S/W we have.
 
Possible solution which can be checked by cable-rules-plugin.phar team are like,
 
1.	To get rid of the problem permanently we could use something like https://github.com/humbug/php-scoper
 
php-scoper add-prefix
This will prefix all relevant namespaces in code found in the current working directory. The prefixed files will be accessible in a build folder. You can then use the prefixed code to build your PHAR.
or 
 
2.	As discussed over call we can ask cable-rules-plugin.phar team for upgrade of PSR/LOG version to 3.0.0
;;;

column1: FAST-848 OSF | Wave 9.2 | ACC | Regression | Telesales | DSL orders are failing with a Sky Ticket when selecting the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Phonebook Entry"
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 

Channel: Telesales

Failed orders: 1167691, 1167679, 1167685,

 

+Please note:+
 # The bug does not appear in Retail (OSF Order ID: 1167699; Barcode: VDE7602957626)
 # The bug does not appear for orders with standard phonebook entry (OSF Order ID: 1167687; Barcode: VDE5602957608)

 

{+}Actual result{+}: DSL orders are failing with a Sky Ticket when selecting the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Phonebook Entry"

 

+Expected result:+ DSL should not fail with a Sky Ticket when selecting the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Phonebook Entry"

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to OSF on ACC2 
 * search for a DSL address, e. g.: "Johanneskirchner Str. 1 a, 85774 Unterföhring"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> DSL & Glasfaser Produkte"
 * select any DSL tariff
 * continue with the order until the Access Details
 * select the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Telefonbucheintrag"
 * complete the order
 * OSF Order ID: 1167685

– > Sky Ticket is created

*Service Name*
Tivano
 
*Error Code*
406
 
*Error Description*
[HTTPAdaptor] Can not connect to HTTP Server[dsllte-api-it.internal.vodafone.com:443], Status[406], Message[INVALID_INPUT_DATAinvalidorder/product/custom-phonebook-data/directory-assistancemust not be nullOrder data could not be validated]
 

Reference ticket for omnius:

OS-67375 OSF | Wave 9.2 | Regression | Telesales | DSL orders are failing with a Sky Ticket when selecting the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Phonebook Entry" - Vodafone Global Jira

 
h2. Solution Design for required OGW fix

In case an extended phone book entry is requested by OSF, the complex element “custom-phonebook-data” as part of the eShop order request has to be used. This element requires at least the following mandatory elements provided within this (including further mandatory elements required): See attached .xlsx and the related order.xsd attached for documentation and verification purpose.
 * For SKU 'SDE01' additional phonebook-data either via element 'standard-phonebook-data' or 'custom-phonebook-data' is mandatory.
 * For SKUs 'SDE02', 'SDE03' an element 'custom-phonebook-data' is mandatory, element 'standard-phonebook-data' is not allowed.
 * The element 'standard-phonebook-data' is only allowed for customers of type 'private'.
 * Customers of type 'soho' or 'business' need to use the element 'custom-phonebook-data', element 'standard-phonebook-data' is not allowed.
 * The element 'custom-phonebook-data' has sub elements 'section' and 'keyword' that are mandatory for customers of type 'soho' or 'business', but are not allowed for customers of type 'private', see below.

h2. Mapping enhancements for "custom-phonebook-data"

For to  better readability, please refer to attached documents
 * [^MappingToDSLandTivano_v8_extendedPhoneBookEntry.xlsx]
 * ^[^eShop order.xsd]^

^!image-2025-05-15-09-10-12-420.png|width=550,height=253!^

column1: OSF | Wave10.0 | ACC1 | All tariffs remain visible in the configurator even after the required tariff has been added to the shopping cart for Mobile SOHO mit RV and Business mit RV customer types.
column41:
We have observed, All tariffs remain visible in the configurator even after the required tariff has been added to the shopping cart for Mobile SOHO mit RV and Business mit RV customer types due to this issue, In case agent added sim only tariff in shopping cart, Omnius is showing an error message in extended shopping cart, Please find below screenshots.

!image-2025-04-28-16-27-17-658.png|width=505,height=251!

!image-2025-04-28-16-28-46-907.png|width=505,height=252!

!image-2025-04-28-16-32-14-868.png|width=503,height=253!

!image-2025-04-28-16-33-39-404.png|width=502,height=261!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales or Retail channel.
 # Select SOHO Private with RV or SOHO Business with RV.
 # Select Tariff in Configurator.
 # Observed selected tariff along with other tariffs visible in configurator.

Actual: All Tariff's are visible in configurator even after required tariff is added in shopping cart for Mobile SOHO mit RV & Business mit RV Customer types.

Expected: Only the selected tariff should be visible in the configurator for Mobile SOHO mit RV & Business mit RV Customer types (same as Private, SOHO Private without RV, SOHO Business without RV).

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2025-04-28-16-14-20-325.png|width=970,height=510!
column324: Agent can create Invalid Mobile package in shopping cart as Incorrect product combination shown in configurator for creating package.
column569:
This is not considered as a bug. The same behaviour exists currently in production and there were no related changed in PCAT rules. The hardware ruling for skeleton customers is more complex, than for consumer customeres (because of confliction rules for skeleton product / tariff and hardware / tariff relations). 

An easy change via PCAT rules is not possible and would require a CR (with most likely bigger Paps and / or Omnius changes).

column879:
12/May/25 3:41 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;It is about the following general configurator mechanism:

When you select a product from package subtype “Device” or “Tariff” or even “Sknum” then the selected item is added to the shopping cart and all other products from the same subtype become invisible. And when you want to change your selection again then you first have to deselect the product, and all other products become visible again. So far so good.

For customer types SOHO/RV and Firma/RV this only works for the first package subtype “Sknum” but not for the subsequent subtypes "Device" and "Tariff".

Actually, there is
 * no related comp rules/CRAC which might define this behavior
 * no mutually exclusive category defined

Assumption:

The defined default cardinality of the package subtype could the reason for the above mechanism. 
|*package_subtype_id*|*package_subtype_name*|*package_subtype_gui_sorting*|*default_cardinality*|
|Sknum|Rahmenvertrag|10|*{color:#de350b}0...1{color}*|
|Device|Hardware|20|*{color:#de350b}1...1{color}*|
|Tariff|Tarif|30|*{color:#de350b}1...1{color}*|
|Option|Optionen|40|0...n|
|Discount|Gutschriften und Aktionen|50|0...n|
|Footnote|Besonderheiten zu Ihrem Tarif|60|0...n|
|Fee|Sonstiges|70|0...n|
|ConfigurableCheckoutOptions|Checkout Products|80|0...n|
|Services|Services|90|0...n|

Question is still why this does not work for skeleton customers.

 ;;;

column885:
19/May/25 4:40 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Shruti Kanchan added a comment -
 
 
 
Timo as suggested this to Thomas Wermke to modify the PCAT

Hi Thomas and Shruti,

 

As far as it is known to me, whether other products are shown under the same package_subtype after selecting a product of that subtype depends on compatibility rules and not on the attribute ‘default_cardinality’ (or other cardinality rules).

 

‘Default_cardinality’ and ‘ilsblu_cardinality’ are only evaluated while proceeding from configurator to extended shopping cart. At that moment it is evaluated if the shopping cart content adheres to the cardinality rules (and thus, not during configuration in configurator).

 

See below example of DSL. The frontend displays other tariffs after selecting the tariffs although the ‘default_cardinality’ is 1…1.

 

 

 

 

@Thomas Wermke Please double check the rule with operation ‘not allowed’ where the behavior is not as you expect (or check with DSL reference data team how it is configured there).

 

@Shruti Kanchan Please check with development after the check of Thomas if it is still not in line with what is expected.

column877:
22/Apr/25 4:48 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback from Simon Auch:

TL;DR: The issue observed by OSF (no products visible in configurator) was caused by an infrastructure component of the kubernetes cluster BLES runs in, not by BLES.

Requests from Omnius and IBP to BLES both had the issue that sometimes the request was rejected with a "401 unauthorized" error, returned by an nginx.

The path of a request from IBP/Omnius to BLES looks roughly like:
 * IBP/Omnius
 * ConHub
 * NGinx
 * BLES

The credentials for all requests to BLES are checked by the nginx instance directly in front of it and, therefore, this was not an issue with BLES.

Since the nginx checks the credentials and 401 errors are related to authorization, I checked the nginx logs. There I found errors indicating that one of the nginx pods (the nginx deployment consists of 3 pods) ran out of disk space. I then checked which pod was out of disk space and killed it, causing Kubernetes to reschedule a new pod to replace it. This fixed the issue.

Follow up steps I see for the infrastructure Teams:
 * improve monitoring for the nginx deployments
 * figure out why this pod was not detected as unhealthy by kubernetes on its own and change it
 * try to find out why the disk was full in the first place
 * retrospectively:
 ** why was it determined to not be an infrastructure issue?
 ** raise awareness for the criticality of cloud components in the system teams;;;
column878: 22/Apr/25 5:01 PM;tanvi.bagade@vodafone.com;Issue resolved, therefore closing the ticket;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Mobile SOHO ILS with addition of "Vodafone E-MailConnect Europe" option on existing "Vodafone Zuhause FestnetzFlat" tariff orders are failing wit "The SOC 'GPRS_BBEU' is not allowed for this subscriber" error in KIAS
column41:
We have observed, Mobile SOHO ILS with addition of "Vodafone E-MailConnect Europe" option on existing "Vodafone Zuhause FestnetzFlat" tariff, orders are failing wit "The SOC 'GPRS_BBEU' is not allowed for this subscriber" error in KIAS.

Please find below screenshot:

!image-2025-04-17-15-39-28-999.png|width=509,height=310!

*Error Message:*

 
 
{{:ROOT xsi:schemaLocation="http://amdocs/vfde/order/VFDESetOrderStatusInput" xmlns:vfdecommon="http://amdocs/vfde/common/VFDECommonTypes" xmlns:vf="http://amdocs/vfde/order/VFDESetOrderStatusInput" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"> <Event> <Type>SetOrderStatus</Type> <ID>12247137</ID> <CallerID>OGW</CallerID> <MessageCreationTimestamp>2025-04-17T09:42:02.467+0200</MessageCreationTimestamp> </Event> <DATA> <OGWSubOrderId>1984325</OGWSubOrderId> <OGWOrderLineId>1005618949</OGWOrderLineId> <Status>InProgress-Failed-OpenExternalTicket</Status> <ErrorCategory>Business</ErrorCategory> <ErrorCode>EAI000039</ErrorCode> <ErrorDescription>An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-MaintainSOC WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI000039, Error_Message: Unspecified application error. Please contact system support., Error_Type: Functional, Error_Sevirity: E, Error_Information: The SOC 'GPRS_BBEU' is not allowed for this subscriber (with SOC_GROUP_CD = '23Z8DE'),Backend Error Code: 9999]</ErrorDescription> <AdditionalInfo> <AttributeCode>ASSIGN_ROLE</AttributeCode> <AttributeValue>APP-DE-OSF_OGW_Retail_Business_Queue</AttributeValue> </AdditionalInfo> </DATA> </vf:ROOT>}}

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Search existing Mobile SOHO customer which is having Vodafone Zuhause FestnetzFlat tariff.
 # Clicks on Modify package.
 # Add Vodafone E-MailConnect Europe option.
 # Submit order and check KIAS response.

*Actual Result :* Mobile SOHO ILS with addition of "Vodafone E-MailConnect Europe" option on existing "Vodafone Zuhause FestnetzFlat" tariff orders are failing wit "The SOC 'GPRS_BBEU' is not allowed for this subscriber" error in KIAS.

*Expected Result:* If Vodafone E-MailConnect Europe option is not compatible for Vodafone Zuhause FestnetzFlat tariff, Then PCAT should not show this option in configurator for agent selection.

column875: 26/Apr/25 12:00 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Hi [~thomas.wermke@vodafone.com] [~kevin.broeggelwirth@vodafone.com] Can you please check this issue.;;;
column876:
28/Apr/25 6:21 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;It looks like that the KIAS data in PAPS was not syncronized recently. While in PCAT the SKU KGPRS_BBEU is still allowed for ILS with tariff VFZH24FFN, in KIAS the SOC was added to the forbidden-SOC-group 23Z8DE for the same on 2025-03-10 16:10:48.

[~tasneem.sattar@vodafone.com]: could you pleaae run KIAS data sync in PAPS. (esp. table MMC_SOC_GROUP_RELATION is important here) 

Afterwards we will need to run another PAPS Import and redeliver the PCAT to ACC1.

 ;;;
column877: 02/May/25 11:24 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;As per the latest updates from [~tasneem.sattar@vodafone.com], They are still analyzing this issue.;;;
column878:
07/May/25 10:24 PM;thomas.wermke@vodafone.com;According to PAPS team the MMC_SOC_GROUP_RELATION is synchronized with KIAS table MNREFSS2.SOC_GROUP_RELATION where the SOC_GROUP_CD = '23Z8DE' and soc = 'GPRS_BBEU' do not exist. Perhaps this snapshot was even not refreshed recently on KIAS side. In fact, the snapshot REFSSDC450 used in KIAS test envs shows the relevant record. This inconsistency between PAPS data (synced KIAS table MNREFSS2.SOC_GROUP_RELATION) and KIAS test env refdata leads to the SOC plausibility failure in the KIAS backend.

It is no PCAT issue.;;;
column879: 08/May/25 11:55 AM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;Thanks [~thomas.wermke@vodafone.com] for the detailed analysis, [~sneha.wayal1@vodafone.com] Please check with KIAS Team and create ticket on KIAS reference data.;;;
column880:
09/May/25 4:24 PM;thomas.jerke@vodafone.com;Email Connect Europe should not be selectabel in OSF for Zuhause Festnetz tariff.

Fix delivery planned approx. 15.5.25. Update of KIAS table mmc_soc_group_realtion from refnki database (Preprod) in Paps ACC required.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10 | ACC1 | Agent needs to click on Weiter button to call Save Delivery address service in case of adding MultiSIM product on existing customer in Tel/Retail channel.
column41:
While performing addition of MultiSIM number on existing Mobile customer scenario in Tel/Retail channel, We have observed Weiter button is present in checkout after saving new connection data for MultiSIM SIM Number, Due to this issue, Agent have to clicks on Weiter button (to call save delivery service call) to process further to Payment section.

Please find below screenshots for same:

Needs to clicks on Weiter button then SaveDeliveryAddress service call:

!image-2025-04-16-17-03-34-776.png|width=366,height=186!

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
2. Search existing Mobile customer.
3. Clicks on Modify package button.
4. Add New MultiSIM option in shopping cart and proceed to checkout.
5. Clicks on Weiter button in Kundendaten section.
6. Proceed further and add E-sim in MultiSIM and clicks on weiter button.
7. After saving New connection data for MultiSIM again Omnius shows Weiter button to call Save Delivery address service.
8. Clicks on Weiter button and then Omnius display Payment section.

Actual: Agent needs to clicks on Weiter button to call Save Delivery address service incase of adding MultiSIM product on existing customer in Retail channel..

Expected: Save Delivery address service should call automatically incase change product or adding MultiSIM product (Applicable for Retail and E-SIM in Telesales) on existing customer scenario because it's hidden section.

DXL Comments:-
Thank you Andreas.

My understanding so far is that DXL is sending 

External credit class= X

Expected:

External credit class= A

While checking the DXL logs, I found the traceID: 05ebb2da234bfe33d84c9dfc85de89a1

DXL is really  sending 
                                               <ns2:additionalData>
                                                               <ns2:key>externalCreditClass</ns2:key>
                                                               <ns2:value>X</ns2:value>
                                               </ns2:additionalData>

This DXL request is following this schufa rating response:
### POST SOUTHBOUND REST RESPONSE URI:http://js-schufa-rating-adapter.dxl-argocd/checkCreditStandingForCustomer WITH STATUS [200] ### {"state":"SUCCESS","infotext":["X- KI SCOREBEREICH I","ES LIEGEN KEINE DATEN AUS OEFFENTLICHEN VERZEICHNISSEN ODER ZU VERTRAGSWIDRIGEM VERHALTEN VOR"],"fraudPreCheck":{"resultType":"VERARBEITUNGSFEHLER","errorMessage":["{id:PLA0012, text:Feld muss gefüllt sein, detail:GP-Geschaeftsvorgangsreferenz}"]},"schufaReferenceId":"50273634"}

I don’t know which is the business logic for having externalCreditClass set to “X” but if it is not related to the schufa-rating response, I suggest to create a bug ticket and assign it to DXL for a deeper analysis from the development team.

Regards,
Raniero

column894:
11/Jun/25 3:21 PM;daniel.loos@vodafone.com;please be aware of the differences here in the request structure.
[~akhilesh.sawarkar@vodafone.com] the page you shared clearly shows that this request structure is expected:
(example with ID + firstname + lastname)
https://10.70.0.152:3213/api/solsticeCustomerSearch/v1/customer?id=1002123456789&givenName=test&familyName=user

We, on the other hand, are sending ALL parameters even though they are empty -> this is why the request is failing.

the question is for me:
1) Is there a conflict between the search services (cdhSearch vs CustomerSearch -> see logfile "Sending request for service: cdhService"; according to [~shival.gupta1@vodafone.com] the request is being created corretly if the service is "customerSearch")

2) does OSF have to change their request structure?
3) does CDH have to change their request processing?;;;
column895:
12/Jun/25 9:31 PM;akhilesh.sawarkar@vodafone.com;Hi,

I spoke with Shival about the design.

We decided that agents will provide either below params
 * customer number →  *Customer* 
 * contract number→ *Agreement Id*
 * OSF order number  → {*}Product Order External Id{*}{*}{*}

or 
 * First Name
 * Last Name
 * City name
 * Streetname
 * House no.
 * House no. postfix
 * E-mail
 * date if birth

when searching in the customer.

When Omnius calls the CDH API to search customer, it will only send the parameters given in the frontend, ignoring any empty values in the request payload.

I believe Omnius should make these changes.;;;
column896:
12/Jun/25 9:44 PM;daniel.loos@vodafone.com;Hi [~akhilesh.sawarkar@vodafone.com], as you write:
"When Omnius calls the CDH API to search customer, it will only send the parameters given in the frontend, ignoring any empty values in the request payload."

This is the expected behavior but also the reason why this defect ticket exists - because in SIT4 and ACC1 this is not the way it is happening (see also SOLDEFECT-17524).
An RCA what broke the customer search would be appreciated (side effect from php upgrade?) in parallel to a defect fix.
Thank you.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Condition type and Discount code are missing in Hardware file for MultiSIM & Second Delivery usecases.
column41:
While performing MultiSim new activation we observed the below mentioned error in ACC1 environment.

*Error message* - *"condition 3 is incomplete, condition type and ZVFA discount code are missing in hardware file ".*

{*}Test data{*}- 953101

*Steps to reproduce-*
1. Login to omnius via telesales channel.
2. Perform serviceability
3. Add mobile package
4. Select ESIM hardware and tariff
5. Fill the required details

Env : All ACC

*Expected Result:* Correct auftrag ID for Contract Summary and contract documents should be generated successfully in Omnius for all orders.

column1: OSF | Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | All Stack | OMNIUS showing a new dialog window - GigaKombi Prüfung for new activation orders
column41:
While doing Sanity in ACC1 environment, we have observed below GigaKombi pop up in configurator.

Step to Reproduce:
1)Login to Telesales/Retail Channel
2)Configure DSL/Mobile/Cable Package and click on weiter button
3)Verify OMNIUS shows a new dialog window - GigaKombi Prüfung 

Actual Result : OMNIUS shows a new dialog window - GigaKombi Prüfung 

Expected Result :  OMNIUS should not shows a new dialog window - GigaKombi Prüfung 

 

Note : In order to switch off the capability of this epic(GigaKombi Liberation (PPM 666899) we need to assign blocking permission BLOCK_GKL to all roles in ACC1 environment.

Mail sent to User Management Team
column324: Agent can be mislead via new dialog window - GigaKombi Prüfung
column569: To disable Gigakombi Liberation functionality we needed to assign blocking permission BLOCK_GKL to all Users

I did some analysis and found that the issue is with Tech M(added comments in defect also)—where they need to fix the correct value send in source system tag—as per design shall send only below values from below 
OSF.TCP,
OSF.TNC,

column1: OSF | Wave 9.2.1, Wave 10.0 | ACC1 | Regression: In case of 500 error for MTAN, an incorrect window is getting shown up
column41:
While Authenticate customer using MTAN we observed that MTAN code window to authenticate customer using MTAN is not visible directy skip SPIN button is visible

Steps to reproduce :

Permission to 360 view agent role : MTAN + SPIN_CAB or SPIN_MOB + 20FX authentication

1.Login to Omnius in Telesales/Ret channel (with 360 view agent role)
2.Search Existing Mobile  Private Postpaid customer
3.Verify Customer search result on search result page.
4. Authentication window will be displayed .
5.As DXL is down we will get 500 error in BE
6.If call is unsuccessful MTAN service sends MTAN to selected MSISDN and returns success code (500)
7.Directly 20FX window will appear to authenticate customer with an error code 

*Actual Result:* MTAN is not working due to Error 500, the next possible authentication should be shown for the agent, without any windows shown in between.

*Expected Result :* In case we get Error 500, the expectation is that agent can authenticate the customer via 2OFX
column324:
Incorrect window (skip SPIN window) is shown in UI. 
Isuue only appears when DXL returns Error 500- the agent must click away 2 windows (skip SPIN & select Skip Reason) to be able to authenticate the customer via 2OFX.
column569:
RCA: MTAN window was not visible due to a conflict with the SpinMobileCab Authentication flow, which triggered an unexpected window overlay

column1: OSF | Wave 9.2 | ACC2 | Omnius is not sending Porting provider in process order request in case of Second delivery on existing porting customer which is leading order failure in submit order request.
column41:
While performing *Second Delivery* on existing porting customer, we observed Porting orders are failed in initial queue.

 

*Steps to Re-produce:*
1. Login to Omnius via Telesales channel.
2. Load existing porting customer, Perform second delivery.
3. Add hardware.
4. Proceed to checkout.
5. Fill required details.

6. Submit the order.

 

*Actual Result:*  Porting provider is missing in connection data section.

*Expected Result:* Porting provider should present in connection data section.

*Test Data:*

Order ID: 1183095

BAN: 119043013

 

*Error:*

An error occurred while processing the message, refer to the details section for more information Message ID: \{D83E539D-8C61-48B4-8AF8-ABF026BEFD81} Instance ID: \{2EDEA04D-1E24-48F7-BA14-8DD221687445} Error Description: There was a failure executing the send pipeline: "Common.Pipelines.SendPipelines.ContextValidatePassThruSendPipeline, Middleware.Framework.Common.Pipelines, Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=8dd4820aa48e7df7" Source: "XML validator" Send Port: "VFDE_OGW_SubmitOrder" URI: "[https://osf-otype1-01-acc2.vodafone.de:8191/VFDESubmitOrderEG/VFDE"|https://osf-otype1-01-acc2.vodafone.de:8191/VFDESubmitOrderEG/VFDE%22] Reason: The XML Validator failed to validate. Details: The 'CarrierID' element is invalid - The value '' is invalid according to its datatype 'String' - The actual length is less than the MinLength value..

 

Note: While retesting this defect, we will execute OS-65619 Test.
column324: Porting provider is missing, it's impacting on second delivery order as it's failing in initial queue
column569:

column41:
Hello

While performing mobile scenario we observed that sliding changes are not showing correctly in shopping cart, extended shopping cart and in contract summary.

Scenario Name:

 

Step to reproduce:
 # logging to retail/tele
 # configure mobile package
 # add one number option for that tariff
 # do checkout
 # Enter customer details
 # Submit order

 

Actual Result: sliding changes are not showing correctly in shopping cart, extended shopping cart and in contract summary.

 

Expected Result: sliding changes should be showing correctly in shopping cart, extended shopping cart and in contract summary.

18/Feb/25 1:32 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Shruti Kanchan added a comment - 
hi [~nasir.sayyad@vodafone.com] 
 
The sliding calculator will reflect when PCAT provides the same.

Example Hardware SKU - KSM2XSH05 used in this case is not a DF hardware and does not have Device_Financing_Duration so no End Period is captured for this SKU

!image-2025-02-18-13-31-06-116.png!

SImilarly the OneNumber Option with SKU KONENUMBERrc1_5 does not have Sliding Calculator Value in the PCAT

!image-2025-02-18-13-31-41-948.png!

Since these are not populated in PCAT it does not reflect in the extended shopping cart of Submit order. So there is no fix from Omnius since it is not an issue at Omnius side.;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.2 | ACC2/IT | Markers are getting highlighted for deselected tariff options for Gigakombi ILS orders
column41:
We have observed that for GigaKombi ILS orders Markers are getting highlighted for deselected tariff options.

 

*Test Data:*

Customer ID: 001940970767, 001910964012

 

*Step to reproduce:*

1)Login to Omnius with Telesales/Retail channel.

2)Search and load an existing GigaKombi customer.

3)Click on Paket andern.

4)Change the tariff.

5)Select one Tarif option under Sprach-Optionen Mobilfunk & Festnetz section.

6)Now select another Tarif option.

7)Validate that after changing the selection of tariff option marker is still highlighted for the deselected option.

 

*Actual Result:* Markers are getting highlighted for deselected tariff options for Gigakombi ILS orders.

*Expected Result:* Markers should only get highlighted for selected tariff options and not for deselected tariff options for Gigakombi ILS orders.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.2 | ACC2 | "Rechnung/Invoice" field is selectable on payment method option on existing customer for second delivery
column41:
While performing Second Delivery on existing customer, we observed "Rechnung/Invoice" field is selectable when clicking on IBAN section on existing customer.

 

I have added Test document for reference.

[^Test Document for second delivery.docx]

 

*Steps to Re-produce:*
1. Login to Omnius via Telesales channel.
2. Load existing customer, perform second delivery.
3. Add hardware having Psim and Esim(optional) should available.
4. Proceed to checkout.
5. Fill required details.
6. Go on payment details page.
7. Payment method delivery is in read and write mode. (Both options are selectable and already enabled)

 

*Actual Result:*  Payment method is in read and write mode, agent is able to change payment method 

*Expected Result:* Payment method should not be editable mode.

 

*Test Data:*

119040612
column324: Agent can change payment method; second delivery flow will lead to create a failure in order
column569:

RCA Original US not implemented correctly payment section data needs to be shown from customer install base, in actual it was taken from previous order checkout data.

column41:

Channel: Telesales

 # The bug does not appear in Retail (OSF Order ID: 1167699; Barcode: VDE7602957626)
 # The bug does not appear for orders with standard phonebook entry (OSF Order ID: 1167687; Barcode: VDE5602957608)

 

{+}Actual result{+}: DSL orders are failing with a Sky Ticket when selecting the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Phonebook Entry"

 

+Expected result:+ DSL should not fail with a Sky Ticket when selecting the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Phonebook Entry"

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to OSF on ACC2 
 * search for a DSL address, e. g.: "Johanneskirchner Str. 1 a, 85774 Unterföhring"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> DSL & Glasfaser Produkte"
 * select any DSL tariff
 * continue with the order until the Access Details
 * select the value "Erweitert/Abweichend" in the field "Telefonbucheintrag"

 * complete the order
 * OSF Order ID: 1167691

406

column876:
07/Feb/25 8:48 PM;dimitrinka.kisimova@vodafone.com;eShop analysis 

The error message is pretty clear. The element "directory-assistance" is mandatory if you provide the tag "custom-phonebook-data"

But the OSF request includes only part of the mandatory elements for "custom-phonebook-data"

column1: OSF | Wave9.2 | ACC2 | Additional Telephone number missing in customer data when BO Agent retrieves saved offer.
column41:
While performing "Multistack New activation of Mobile postpaid and DSL in Telesales channel with save offer (send to BO)" scenario, We have observed, Additional Telephone number missing in customer data when BO Agent retrieves saved offer.

Please find below screenshots:

Additional Telephone Number added in customer data section for Festnetz:

!image-2025-01-29-15-51-26-217.png|width=338,height=419!

!image-2025-01-29-15-53-23-252.png|width=334,height=328!

!image-2025-01-29-15-56-19-546.png|width=342,height=193!

Retrieve offer and check Customer data overview section:

Twice City Name shown in Delivery address overview section:

!image-2025-01-29-16-01-14-144.png|width=341,height=339!

Steps to Reproduce:1
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales channel.
 # Create Multipackage Mobile with DSL New Activation package in shopping cart.
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Add Additional Phone Numbers in Customer data section (contact data).
 # Select PDT in Delivery section.
 # Save offer (Send to BO).
 # Retrieve offer and check Customer data overview section and Delivery overview section.

Actual:

column1: OSF | Wave9.2 | ACC2 | Omnius is showing customer address for second package in Delivery section instead of shop address if agent refresh checkout page and continue sales flow.
column41:
We have observed, Omnius is showing customer address for second package in Delivery section instead of shop address if agent refresh checkout page and continue sales flow.

Please find below screenshots:

Select PDT (DHL Packstation) for first and package and continue same shop address for second package:

!image-2025-01-28-19-46-18-217.png|width=325,height=322!

Agent Refresh Omnius page on Voicelog page, Agent reach to delivery section and select DHL Packstation again:

!image-2025-01-28-19-46-30-917.png|width=328,height=172!

When agent save Delivery section, Omnius is showing Customer Address instead of shop:

!image-2025-01-28-19-47-54-386.png|width=314,height=302!

When Agent submit order, Delivery address is missing for second package:

!image-2025-01-28-19-50-54-149.png|width=456,height=251!

Steps to Reproduce:
 # Login to Omnius as Telesales Agent.
 # Create Mobile Prepaid Multipackage order (2 packages).
 # Proceed to checkout.
 # Select PDT (DHL Packstation) address for first package and continue same shop address for second package.
 # Agent Refresh Omnius page on Voicelog page, Agent reach to delivery section and select DHL Packstation again.
 # When agent save Delivery section, Omnius is showing Customer Address instead of shop.
 # When Agent submit order, Delivery address is missing for second package.

Actual: Omnius is showing customer address for second package in Delivery section instead of shop address if agent refresh checkout page and continue sales flow.

Expected: Correct Address should be shown in checkout.
column324: Incorrect Delivery Address shown in checkout for PDT delivery option if Agent refresh Omnius session.
column569:
RCA for the defect -
After page refresh, customer address is getting selected as the delivery address instead of shop address due to old, unmatched condition check. The check is no longer required now because the handling is now done through different checks. I removed that check, after that shop address is getting selected as the delivery address.

18/Mar/25 11:10 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Kshitij Kumar Srivastava added a comment - 
 
 
Hello [~pallavi.kokate1@vodafone.com] 

this is not a valid defect. it works as expected.

for billing address dropdown,

there is customer known billing address shown over UI option that received from Customer Ibase, with fixed label *Vorhandene Adresse verwenden* ( address details) and this data shown as readonly mode also dropdown is also in readonly state when validation pass successfully,

if case validation fails then force to choose different address then dropdown state editable and user choose another option from dropdown.

Regards to customer known billing address under summary section system shown the exact Billing data (Contact+Address) as it received from Customer Ibase. 
we found in GetCustomerDetails Mode-1 there is not title data received for billing contact, that is why title info in not shown over summary UI.

mainly it was agreed not to change customer known billing details (contact & Address) in Omnius when Billing data (Contact+Address) are correct. And for that reason in first place it shown in readonly state.;;;

RCA: As part of reset module and update modules we are updating the {{catalog_tables.xml}} table with the complete pcat tables list on webservers when we load application first time after deployment. And this should be in sync on both script and the webservers.

We update file on webserver but we use the file from script server during PLM process is causing this issue.;;;

column892:
22/Jan/25 11:49 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment - 
 
Issue has been discussed with bas and we come to solution, which is as below.

During the populate_additionalDb step we are thinking to update the catalog_tables.xml file as like we do during the resetModule upgrade process.

This should make the update similar and should solve our problem currently we are facing.

 

This change or fix cannot be fixed immediately as it needs quite development and more testing effort after the fix, as we don't have such env setup like ACC where we have separate Web & Script servers maintained. Also this issue should be part of the PROD aswell, may be its not observed on PROD or this feature never used in PROD.

Can you check and share this information if *populate_additionalDb.php* step is ever performed on PROD PLM process?;;;
column893: 23/Jan/25 5:22 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  yes we are performing this step each night in the regular publish process;;;
column894: 27/Jan/25 11:26 AM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Requested Tech M Production team to schedule call with VF OPS to check this on PROD;;;
column895:
29/Jan/25 12:03 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment
 
 
Hi All

I discussed this issue further with Waseem and discussed few possible solution.

Solution: we need to keep the *catalog_tables.xml* file on some central place and create symlink of it on all servers like Web servers, Script Servers, API servers, to avoid file differences between Web & Script servers, etc

Ideally it should be treated/managed to create symlink similar to the Cable artifact file we currently do after pcat import.

*Steps to follow to create symlink.*
 # Ideally we need to perform this Symlink create after the completion of PCAT import on Sandbox environment.

 # Then copy the file from Sandbox environment from the path \{{DOCROOT}}/app/etc/catalog_tables.xml and keep it on some central place

*Note: This copy file and create symlink should happen before we start the Publish activity.(Ideally after completion of PCAT import and before Publish start)*
 # Then start the publish process.

We need to discuss  so that this can be done on ACC and verified. KIndly schedule call for the same;;;
column896: 31/Jan/25 12:46 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;Call is scheduled today with TID Team;;;
column897:
31/Jan/25 4:58 PM;atharva.paskanthi@vodafone.com;*OSF | Wave9.2 | Checkpoint | DM | OS-65820 MoM and Action items (31st January, 2025)*
 
As discussed in call,
- Sunil had discussion with Waseem and suggested a workarounf
- We need to keep catalog_tables.xml file in central place , Need to handle it like cable Artifact file , keep it in shared path
- And need to copy this file from Sandbox and make available to API & Script Servers after PCAT Import
- But to get Permanent Solution Need to reschedule and discuss with Pramodkumar from TID, Sandeep and Waseem from TechM;;;
column898:
03/Feb/25 6:53 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;The issue is caused by the new Package type TV for Fusion C - as we have the parser and the new Fusion C catalogue on both ACC1, ACC2 and in production, the issue happened on all 3 ENV already.

TechM is working on a solution from code and infra side, but its not mandatory for production Go Live Wave 9.2 as issue is already present in production and temporarily solved. Unless no new package type will come up, it should not fail anymore.

Issue is caused by the solution for faster PCAT Publish (reduction of the publish downtime). Within this solution there is a design gap

reset modules are running on the application but its getting updated on Webservers only -> files on the script servers are not updated. There is a configuration in backend to connect to Webserver or Scriptserver and for security reasons we need to get the files from Scriptservers and cannot take it from Webservers

-> Solution will be prepared by TechM, once its ready we align on a testing slot as we should not disturb release test activities in remaining last 2 weeks;;;

column923:
12/May/25 7:10 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Latest feedback from TechM:

*Issue:*

This issue occurred due to mismatch in table on Sandbox and script server. The mismatch happened because “catalog_tables.xml” update on sandboxes is not reflected on other server.

 

{*}Solution{*}:

As part of this solution  we create a Symlink of  “catalog_tables.xml” and put in a central location so that  central location has always have updated   file of  “catalog_tables.xml”, whenever deployment will happen on other server it will pick this file “catalog_tables.xml”  from  central location  and not from pkg itself  so that other server will have  Web, Script & API etc will have updated file as well  so that when plm run from script server it will not  have mismatch of table issue  due to updated file there.

 

{*}Impact{*}: it will not have any impact since tested in ST but ACC we can see once deployment will be done.;;;

column937:
13/Jun/25 12:16 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Latest feedback from Waseem:

Based on the latest call below is the solution:

OSE deployment on Sandbox:
 # Check if catalog_tables.xml is present under the shared location (for example in ACC1: /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/)
 # IF file is present, then create a symlink for the file in app/etc/catalog_tables.xml towards sharedpath/catalog_tables.xml for example in ACC1: /opt/SP/WEB_DATA/ACC1/omnius/osf-dintib-acc1/app/etc/catalog_tables.xml is symlinked to /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/catalog_tables.xml file.
 # IF file is not present then COPY the catalog_tables.xml file from the tar package to the shared location (for example in ACC1 on the location /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/catalog_tables.xml) and then create a symlink same as step 2.
 # *Either step 2 is taken or step 3, app/etc/catalog_tables.xml file should always be a symlink to the sharedlocation/catalog_tables.xml file at the end of SANDBOX deployment.*

OSE deployment on webser, api server, script server or any deployment other than SANDBOX deployment.
 # Create a symlink for the file app/etc/catalog_tables.xml to the file present in the sharedlocation/catalog_tables.xml. For example on ACC1 the file /opt/SP/WEB_DATA/ACC1/omnius/osf-telesales-int-acc1/app/etc/catalog_tables.xml is symlinked to /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/catalog_tables.xml file

This will ensure that the changes done to catalog_tables.xml during PLM is also available in the webserver or script or api as the change is done to the file on the sharedlocation.


-> permanent solution Kevin is working on;;;

column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 

Channel: Telesales + Retail

DSL PCAT: OSF-20241027_Version_391_FN_2024_10_10

Test data: 001956928712

 

*Please note:* this bug is already in Production

 

{+}Actual result{+}: A Sky ticket is created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory – > Missing *refComponentId in Component for SecureNet*

 

+Expected result:+ No Sky ticket should be created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * search for a DSL customer with SecureNet in the inventory on ACC1, e.g.: 001956928712
 * click on "Meine Produkte >> DSL package >> Paket ändern"
 * select a new DSL tariff, e. g.: "[R708.2000000020-24] GigaZuhause 250 DSL"
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > "[I1414ISN01] Secure Net+" and "[GS_SN_3x3_99[br]] 3 Monate Rabatt auf Secure Net+" stay in the inventory – > *OK*

!image-2024-10-15-10-42-19-205.png!
 * create the order

OSF Order ID: 889055

– > Sky Ticket is created

*Service Name*
FNSubmitOrder
 
*Error Code*
SIDCOM-ERROR
 
*Error Description*
An error was encountered while invoking FN-CreateFNPOrder WS. Details [Error_Code: SIDCOM-ERROR, Error_Message: ERROR COM0000: Sorted SOM is INVALID! nullcvc-complex-type.4: Attribute 'ID' must appear on element 'secureNet'., Error_Type: , Error_Sevirity: , Error_Information: ]

 

[~marco.abraham01@vodafone.com] has already analyzed the bug:

 
 * at ILS no information about SecureNet is provided to the Backend (Also at a cancellation of SecureNet nothing os provided to the Backend)

 * missing refComponentId in Component for SecureNet in RetrieveCustomerInfo - Mode2 logs

For *other components* there is a refComponentId, e. g.:  

!image-2024-10-15-11-00-06-711.png!

For the SecureNet component there is no refComponentId. There should be a refComponentId *10* for SecureNet, like:

!image-2024-10-15-11-01-38-816.png!

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | GeteSIMInformation service is not triggering for S2S multi order line update
column41:
While performing New activation of Esim compatible with as shipping order deliver to your own shop flow , We have observed,  GeteSIMInformation request is not triggering for E-SIM with Ship2Store order in case of multiple order line ids.

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Add more than one E-SIM compatible Package and Proceed to checkout.
 # Select E-SIM in New connection section.
 # Select Shipping order - Delivery to your own shop
 # Submit order and send for VORAS processing
 # Observe OrderLineID is missing in setorder status after BE processing

 

 

*Actual Result:*  GeteSIMInformation request is not triggering for E-SIM

*Expected Result:* GeteSIMInformation request should trigger

 

(Raised the ticket for tracking purpose)

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version
column41:
*Description:* For UM Scenario we observed issue as BEW version is not updating in Backend and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version.

 

*Test Data:*

281507501

*documentID:* 10832608

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Retail channel as FI/PA agent.
Search existing *UM* customer with ADV and DEV version less than 4.
Retrieve the customer and click on BEW Bearbeiten button.
Verify BEW banner notification.
Select BEW ERFASSEN.
Select checkbox for ADV/DEV.
Click on "Dokument erstellen"(Create document) button
Document will be generated.
After that search the customer again.
select BEW Bearbeiten button.
BEW Erfassen button should not available/disable.

 

*Actual Result:* BEW version is not updating in Backend and BEW Erfassen is enable, even after update the version.

*Expected Result:* BEW version should be update in Backend and BEW Erfassen button should be disable after updating the version.

 

*Reference Defect:*

[OS-56676]

11/Jul/24 7:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  based on the latest calls e have the following findings for Retail BEW and unitymedia in general

1) New customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

2) Existing customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

3) Existing customer, Retail, BEW only ->{color:#de350b} *Backend receives and stores BEW correctly? Please confirm this*
{color:#172b4d}What is wrong in all cases -> Frontend OSF is not able to retrieve the right BEW settings. So if BEW was updated in UNitymedia backend, Frontend is not reflecting this. It still looks like no BEW is set{color} ** 
{color:#172b4d}We will also compare the same for VKD, how Retrievecustomerinfo Mode 3 related to BEW permissions is looking like{color}{color};;;
column884:
12/Jul/24 7:08 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  the ticket itself is only for Unitymedia, so for VKD its not a problem and no ticket reported.

We still need to document here, if the Existing customer, Retail, BEW only for Unitymedia is reaching the backend as ticket says 

_*{color:#de350b}BEW version is not updating in Unity Backend{color}* and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version._

 

At the moment we assume, BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but we cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version 
Unitymedia is handling permissions with Version 2, OGW expecting Version  4 and for retrieval of existing permissions we get Version 0.

Needs to be checked with responsible person from MinervaAdapter (VKD side);;;
column885: 17/Jul/24 2:34 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;No progress yet as we did not identify the responsible person who can help with Minerva Adapter VKD ;;;
column886:
18/Jul/24 9:28 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;I have enclosed the latest discussion.
As per latest analysis this problem is related to the way back from Unitymedia via Minerva Adapter VKD to OGW

{color:#de350b}*OK:*{color} OGW version 4 -> Minerva Adapter maps Version 4 from the VKD request into Version 2 for the request to UME/VFW -> UME/VFW is storing Version 2 correctly in Mood and showing right entries in RNS for the customer 

{color:#00875a}*Not OK*{color}: Now when we open the customer who has given BEW again in OSF, we expect that the stored BEW is taken and we are not asked to capture BEW again. Problem: For this get_permission Call we are receiving version 0 for the mentioned scenarios and we cannot map this version to our valid Version 4 (not OK)

{+}*Gap*{+}: We need a Mapping: UME/VFW is sending back Version 2 to Minerva Adapter-> Minerva Adapter maps Version 2 to Version 4 if getpermission request is coming from OGW

 

I have shared the feedback also with Jörg Trierweiler, Thomas Schneider, Andreas Baldermann and few more people to verify.
This is a general topic and not specifically related to BEW only Retail Epic
Waiting for feedback about possible next steps;;;

column900:
18/Apr/24 12:36 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas with following outcome:
 * Values like "AccountCategory" in Omnius are derived from OGW: Here:- _AccountCategory_ in getCustomerResult for index search and _Region_ in retrieveCustomerInfo mode1 for LegacySearch.
 * As the ADDRESS REGION is in UM Area - it is treated as UM customer, even though he belongs to the VKD Stack

h4. _Possible SD option to be validated/proven:_ 
 * Derive customer stack from GlobalID prefix ("legacy stack")  instead of address region
 * IF improvements required as this is only known by OGW (Omnius can only see LK_ from linked customers) - e.g. introducing new attribute to indicate customers product stack:
 * CustomerSearch()
 * getCustomerDetails()
 * [@Mitra, Gaurab, External Vendor|mailto:gaurab.mitra@amdocs.com]: We should investigate if further interfaces have to be considered (To be discussed on next CR meeting)

[@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: To check UseCases in Omnius to be considered for an improvement

Further benefit: Omnius Performance increase If product stack information is directly provided by OGW 

 

So team is working on possible solution but will take some time ;;;

24/Jan/24 3:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  I was not creating any order, I am just scanning portal UI tool from time to time to find unidentified issues. And within this quality check I have found tickets with this error message. 

 

After some analysis I have identified, that it seems to be this scenario:

-> Search existing unitymedia customer and perform Move to VKD adress 

 

this is example Order ID from ACC1 - it failed with 2 sky tickets

One ticket because of invalid VPKN (issue is solved, please ignore that) and second sky ticket was for setpermission.


Unfortunately Sky ticket were cleared in between so I am not able to find my two tickets anymore..... But hopefully you can reproduce on your environment for a Move from Unity to VKD.

Seems like in this case the existing customer ID from unity is taken over, instead of recognizing that customer will get a new customer ID from VKD for Move scenario

 

Order ID 782545, Customer ID 1009755201 (initial customer before Move) 

!image-2024-01-24-11-21-17-927.png!

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF Wave 8.1 | ACC2 |Existing customer scenario with GigaKombi does not work
column41:
Testenvironement: Test1b/ACC2

Testrun: Code Freeze regression testing OSF for PCAT Cable

Description: An existing customer cannot do anything with gigakombimarkers like VB4/VB5/VA1.
Always an errormessage appears in the extended shopping cart (see screenshot) and no further step is possible

Failed testcases:
[https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/SYSSHARQS-1699]

Small description of Teststeps:
Testcustomer: *934829320* (has an old TV product CGT1WG1)
Open OSF ACC2 Telesales
Load Testcustomer
Add a mobile tariff like *[KGM1LH30] GigaMobil L mit PremiumSmartphoneSpecial (Sub 30)*
With hardware "{*}[S00302349] Oppo Find X3 Pro Navy Blue - M{*}"
Go to the existing products of the customer
and click on Paket ändern
TV is opened
Select VB4 as gigakombi - marker
In small shopping cart gigakombi marker appears correctly
in extended shopping cart gigakombi marker appears but error message is thrown (see screenshot)

On ACC1/test3b the same test works correctly
column569: Logic for Gigakombi was changed & there is no GigaKombi available for TV. The markers VB4 + VB5 are not booked anymore. Also for KIP there wsa a change. VA1 was replaced with GKF and GKF is not booked for existing customers. Therefore the defect is not reproducible anymore
column869: As a workaround the agent can trigger execution of the posting rules by selecting and deselecting any product.
column874:
21/Nov/23 6:51 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;Analysis results:

To prevent more issues related to [[OTF-902] KIPOPENEDMARKER not being sent in submit order xml || ADD and Drop Cable backend error - Vodafone Global Jira|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OTF-902] we improved the detection of empty packages in OSF to prevent the agent from entering the checkout with such.

In this case however the package is not empty as it contains VB4. As such our rule should not trigger if the posting rules were executed correctly after clicking the button to create the GigaKombi bundle.

This issue must be fixed by OSF - the posting must be executed after the bundle is created and a product (like VB4) is added to the package.;;;
